column12: MEJORAS INTRODUCIDAS EN EL OBJETO DE LA SOLICITUD DE PATENTE DE INVENCION ESPAÑOLA N. P9802176 POR "PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA OBTENCION DE POLVO DE METALES PRECIOSOS APLICABLE COMO COMPONENTE AUXILIAR DE PERFUMES, ESENCIAS Y SIMILARES.
column13: Mejoras introducidas en el objeto de la solicitud de patente de invención n° P9802176 por "procedimiento para la obtención de polvo de metales preciosos aplicable como componente auxiliar de perfumes, esencias y similares". Las mejoras comprenden el empleo de: (I) el metal precioso a transformar en forma de láminas, panes u obleas, (II) un medio de molturación que comprende un sistema de cuchillas movidas por un eje central de giro y de movimiento vertical ascenso-descendente, un motor y, opcionalmente, unos medios de refrigeración o de calentamiento exterior; (III) una solución hidroalcohólica constituida por agua y etanol, en una concentración superior al 4% en volumen de etanol; y (IV) la superficie media de las partículas de metal precioso obtenidas está comprendida entre 0,00020 mm2 y 0,6 mm2. Estas partículas pueden añadirse a una solución alcohólica o hidroalcohólica tal como un perfume, esencia, cava, champagne, licor o similar.

column12: Process for obtaining precious-metal powder applicable as auxiliary component in perfumes, essences (essential oils)and the like
column13: Process for obtaining fine particles of precious metals applicable as auxiliary component in perfumes, essences and the like, which consists in introducing sheets or leaves of precious metals inside a container with a grinder, an alcoholic or aqueous-alcoholic solution being added, and said leaves or sheets being ground until the leaves or sheets of precious metal are converted into particles of precious metal of small size. The next stage is decantation (settling) and subsequent extraction of the aqueous-alcoholic solution until said solution covers the surface of the product, the remainder being left in a rest stage until the aqueous-alcoholic solution evaporates.

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR CONCEALING BALDNESS
column13: Innocuous pigments, such as those normally employed in cosmetics, are used as basic products, to which are added earths mixed with different iron oxides and dyed with appropriate dyes so that, by combining them conveniently, a range of colours adequate to different types of hair is obtained, the mixing step being followed by a milling operation in order to obtain a fine powder which is completely homogenous from a chromatic point of view. Said powder may be applied directly to the scalp by using a bag or a pad of polyamide or similar which allows the passage of the powder through it when tapping gently the pad on the scalp, or else the powder may be mixed with lacquer to obtain a suspension of the aerosol type applicable to the scalp with a spray type container.
column15: ALONSO VAREA JOSE FERNANDO

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA PREPARACION DE PRODUCTOS PARA LA DISIMULACION DE CALVICIES.
column13: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA PREPARACION DE PRODUCTOS PARA LA DISIMULACION DE CALVICIES. PROCEDIMIENTO PARA LA PREPARACION DE PRODUCTOS PARA LA DISIMULACION DE CALVICIES. EL PROCEDIMIENTO CONSISTE EN COMBINAR RESINAS VINILICAS, DISPERSAS EN ALCOHOL ETILICO, CON UNA MEZCLA DE PIGMENTOS O COLORANTES INORGANICOS DISPERSOS EN ACETATO DE ETILO, AÑADIENDOSE UNA SUBSTANCIA PERFUMANTE DISUELTA EN ALCOHOL ETILICO. LAS RESINAS VINILICAS FORMAN EL 17% DE LA COMPOSICION TOTAL, LOS PIGMENTOS INORGANICOS CONSTITUYEN EL 10% DEL PESO TOTAL, Y EL PERFUMANTE ES EL 0,75% DEL PESO TOTAL. EL TAMAÑO DE LOS PIGMENTOS INORGANICOS DEBE SER INFERIOR A 15 MICRAS, Y LA MEZCLA DE PIGMENTOS INORGANICOS Y/O COLORANTES VARIA EN FUNCION DE LA TONALIDAD DE COLOR QUE SE QUIERA OBTENER, PARA ASEMEJARLO AL COLOR DEL CABELLO. LOS PRODUCTOS SE USAN PARA DISIMULAR CALVICIES, ESPECIALMENTE EN LA ZONA DE LA CORONILLA.
column15: ALONSO VAREA JOSE FERNANDO

column12: Actuation apparatus and method
column13: A force regulated actuation apparatus (3) for a vehicle manual transmission (1) comprises a gearshift input member (5) or gearstick, an actuator assembly (13) for communicating input force from the gearstick to a gear selector device (11a, 11b, 11c); drive means (23) arranged to load the manual gearshift mechanism; and control means (25) for the drive means (23), said control means controlling the output of the drive means to provide a consistent input force to operate the gearstick (5) during gear selection. The drive means (23) may be a linear motor. The vehicle user may be allowed to select from alternative gearshift force profiles ( Fig. 6 ). Force may be applied by the drive means (23) to assist or resist gearchanges, depending on the comparison between force required and force desired. A method for selecting a gear in a manual transmission is also disclosed.

column12: Actuation and method for controlling force required to change gear
column13: A force regulated actuation apparatus 3 for a vehicle manual transmission 1 comprises a gearstick 5, an actuator assembly 13 for communicating input force from the gearstick 5 to a gear selector device 11 a, 11b, 11 c. Drive means 23 arranged to load the manual gearshift mechanism and control means 25 for the drive means 23. column12: Apparatus and method for controlling operation of a vehicle clutch
column13: Apparatus for controlling operation of a vehicle clutch (5) includes a hydraulic clutch actuation system (7) comprising an input actuator (9), an output actuator (11), a conduit (13) for transferring hydraulic fluid between the input and output actuators (9,11) and a valve device (23) for regulating the flow rate of hydraulic fluid between the output and input actuators (9,11). Control means (25) controls the operational status of the valve device (23) according to input values relating to at least one vehicle operating parameter, the apparatus being configured to adjust the valve (23) to control the maximum flow rate of hydraulic fluid between the output and input actuators (9,11) when engaging the clutch (5). Advantages comprise reduced peak torque applied to the clutch; and a smoother ride for vehicle occupants. Smaller components may be used as there is less risk of abuse.

column12: Improvements in and relating to Soles for Footwear.

Soles.-" Alpargatas " or rope soles are made from unspun yarn or the like which is merely twisted in the one direction into bands without being plaited or braided. In one form, the sole comprises a core a wound from a single band of unspun flax, tow, or jute yarn, &c., twisted in the one direction and then compressed, and a reinforcing outer wrapping b of plaited strands. The ends of this wrapping, which may be of a different colour from the core, may be tied together and turned inwardly, as-shown. In another arrangement, the core is made of an inner band of esparto grass, or jute, flax, tow, or other fibres of inferior quality, enclosed in a sheath of jute, flax, tow, &c. of superior quality.

column12: REVESTIMIENTO GENERADOR DE ENERGIA FOTOVOLTAICA.
column13: Revestimiento generador de energía fotovoltaica. Se constituye a partir de un soporte cerámico (1) de los empleados en construcción de exteriores, en cuya cara vista o superior se fijan células fotovoltaicas (3) y se dispone un recubrimiento transparente (9) resistente a los agentes atmosféricos y que deja pasar los rayos solares. En la cara inferior del soporte cerámico (1) se incluye una caja hermética(8) para interconectar las células fotovoltaicas (3)de diferentes soportes cerámicos (1) entre sí. Los soportes cerámicos (1) se montan formando fachadas, tejados, solados y similares, y también pueden montarse para constituir el recubrimiento exterior de cualquier estructura arquitectónica, de modo que se aprovecha la energía solar al máximo, y todo ello de forma que los soportes cerámicos (1) quedan perfectamente integrados en la estética de la construcción arquitectónica.

column13: a presente invenção refere-se a um envidraçamento balísti-co para aplicação veicular, definindo uma superfície externa (20) e uma superfície interna (30), o envidraçamento compreendendo uma combinação de lâminas (4a, 5, 4b, 9) de materiais distintos e camadas intermediárias (6a, 6b, 8) interpostas entre as lâminas (4a, 5, 4b, 9), sendo provido um chanfro (y) em pelo menos uma lâmina mais exter-na (4a), o chanfro (y) definindo um ângulo (¿) voltado para a superfí-cie externa (20) do envidraçamento (1), em que a composição balística do envidraçamento compreende pelo menos uma primeira lâmina in-termediária (5) que corresponde a um inserto ou reforço metálico, de modo que o chanfro (y) facilita o encaixe do envidraçamento na apli-cação, em particular devido ao ângulo (¿) que, além de auxiliar no po-sicionamento e montagem do envidraçamento, permite uma vedação deste com o alojamento do envidraçamento na carroceria do veículo, desse modo evitando infiltrações de água, passagens de ar/vento e trepidações, enquanto a primeira lâmina intermediária (5) de material metálico confere a resistência balística necessária à aplicação.

column12: BULLETPROOF GLAZING FOR USE IN VEHICLES.
column13: The present invention refers to bulletproof glazing for use in vehicles, defining an external surface (20) and an internal surface (30), the glazing comprising a combination of sheets (4A, 5, 4B, 9) of different materials and intermediate layers (6A, 6B, 8) interposed between the sheets (4A, 5, 4B, 9), with a chamfer (Y) being provided in at least one outermost sheet (4A), the chamfer (Y) defining an angle (a) facing the external surface (20) of the glazing (1), where the ballistic composition of the glazing comprises at least one first intermediate sheet (5) which corresponds to a metal insert or support, such that the chamfer (Y) facilitates the fitting of the glazing into the application, in particular due to the angle (a) which, in addition to assisting in the positioning and assembly of the glazing, allows for the sealing thereof with the housing of the glazing in the body of the vehicle, thereby preventing water infiltrations, the passage of air/wind and vibrations, while the first intermediate sheet (5) of metallic material confers the necessary ballistic resistance on the application.

column12: ANTI-EXPLOSION BALLISTIC GLAZING FOR VEHICULAR APPLICATION
column13: This invention concerns anti-explosion ballistic glazing (1), for application preferably to moveable and/or fixed windows of highway, military, and/or off-road vehicles, and agricultural machinery, which comprises an external surface (2) facing the external part of the vehicle or passenger compartment, an internal surface (3) facing the internal part of the vehicle, a combination of at least two sheets (4, 5, 6, 10) and at least two intermediate layers (7, 8, 9) of different materials positioned between the external surface (2) and the internal surface (3), and a chamfer (Y) arranged in parts or along the perimeter of the glazing (1) providing space for the full or partial housing of an overlap (12), which is designed to apply reaction forces to the explosion waves, keeping the glazing (1) in its housing, in addition to facilitating its manufacture, dispensing with the inconveniences of manufacturing a counter-piece and, further, facilitating the installation thereof in the vehicle, requiring fewer adjustments and controls.

Se constituye a partir de un soporte cerámico (1a, 1b) sobre el que se dispone una capa encapsulante (4) sobre la que se ubican células fotovoltaicas (3), y a continuación incluye una segunda capa encapsulante (5), la cual es cubierta por una capa de protección (7), que está constituida por tres capas (9, 10 y 11) que presentan una alta resistencia a los agentes atmosféricos y además permiten el paso de los rayos solares. column12: Structural displacement measurement using unmanned aerial vehicles equipped with lasers
column13: An unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) and laser generator may be used to measure structural displacements. The system may measure relative movement of the UAV and the structure, as well as individual movement of the UAV. The individual movement of the UAV may then be subtracted from the relative movement of the UAV and the structure, in order to accurately calculate structural displacements.

column12: Mesh wrap based on affine-invariant coordinates
column13: Embodiments provide for transferring mesh connectivity. Embodiments include receiving a definition of a correspondence between a first curve for a source mesh and a second curve for a target shape. Embodiments include initializing an output mesh by setting a third plurality of vertices in the output mesh equal to a first plurality of vertices in the source mesh. Embodiments include transforming the output mesh by modifying the third plurality of vertices based on the first curve, the second curve, and a second plurality of vertices of the target mesh. Vertices of the third plurality of vertices that relate to the first curve are conformed to a shape defined by the second curve, and vertex modifications that result in affine transformations of faces in the output mesh are favored. Embodiments include using the output mesh to transfer an attribute from the source mesh to the target shape.

column12: Mechanisms of marking and identification in the level of transportation for the management of caches of contents. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Marking and identification mechanisms at the transport level for the management of content caches. The object of this invention is to define the mechanisms and additional features necessary to support the deployment of content cache services based on the transport level protocol. It provides the necessary marking mechanisms for the identification of content at the transport level, as well as the interception mechanisms that would allow the sending of the contents in cache by intermediate servers. A specific design of these mechanisms is proposed, using the tcp transport protocol. The proposed mechanisms are of direct application in the deployment of communications networks, allowing the creation of generic cache services, independent of the applications that make use of them. column13: The invention relates to the use of prokaryotic beta recombinase in eukaryotic cells, especially for transgenic work in eukaryotic cells. It also relates to the use of prokaryotic beta recombinase for site-specific intramolecular recombination between two six sites in eukaryotic cells. The use of the gene coding for beta recombinase for promoting the deletion of DNA sequences located between directly oriented six sites in mammalian cells and for catalysing site-specific resolution of DNA sequences in an extrachromosomal target introduced into an eukaryotic cell are also disclosed.

column12: Generating three-dimensional virtual tours from two-dimensional images
column13: Interactive three-dimensional (3D) virtual tours are generated from ordinary two-dimensional (2D) still images such as photographs. Two or more 2D images are combined to form a 3D scene, which defines a relationship among the 2D images in 3D space. 3D pipes connect the 2D images with one another according to defined spatial relationships and for guiding virtual camera movement from one image to the next. A user can then take a 3D virtual tour by traversing images within the 3D scene, for example by moving from one image to another, either in response to user input or automatically. In various embodiments, some or all of the 2D images can be selectively distorted to enhance the 3D effect, and thereby reinforce the impression that the user is moving within a 3D space. Transitions from one image to the next can take place automatically without requiring explicit user interaction.

column12: FOOTWEAR ARTICLE FOR PATIENTS WITH PARKINSON'S DISEASE, INTENDED TO PREVENT FREEZING OF GAIT AND FALLS
column13: The invention relates to a footwear article for patients with Parkinson's disease that have an altered gait. According to the invention, the thickness of the sole is increased in the front portion of the foot (1), such that the forefoot support remains elevated in relation to the plane of the sole. The footwear article does not include a heel so that the front portion of the foot is elevated. Two structures (3) extend outwards from the sides of the front portion of the sole, increasing the leading edge (4) and providing two side supports. The lower portion (2) of the tip of the footwear article is bevelled, forming an acute angle in relation to the plane of the sole.

column12: Improvements in and relating to Plaiting or Braiding Machines.
column13: 100,813. Villa, J. Y., and Alonso e Yzaguirre, F. Nov. 19, 1915. Braiding-machines.-In a plaiting or braiding machine in which the thread containers or carriers travel in a. figure-of-eight or other serpentine path and are transferred automatically from one curve to another, the thread-containers a, Fig. 5, are provided at each end with a flange a<1> carrying two catches a<2> and a projection a<3>. The projection a<3> on the lower flange travels in a groove c' Fig. 4, in a plate c. The groove is of the shape shown in Fig. 4, having only one point of intersection. The thread-containers are carried round by disl;s b, Fig. 1, having semicircular openings to accommodate the containers and pins b<2> to engage the catches a<2> on the containers. The shape of the groove c<1> is such that the containers a are given a partial rotation by the double convex segment c<2> to release the catch on one side from the pin of one disk and to engage the catch on the other side with the pin on the other disk. The disks b are driven by bevel-gearing d, d<1> from the main shaft d<2>. The take-up rollers e<1>, e<3> are driven by bevel, worm, and spur gearing from the same shaft. The upper roller e<5> is loose upon its spindle e<3>, which slides on vertical guides e<2>, adjustable springs e<6> providing the requisite pressure. The cores of the plaits are led through openings in the stationary vertical shafts f<2>, which serve as supports for the hollow bushes b<3> of the disks b. A stationary finger may be provided to operate upon the projection on the upper flange of the thread-container.

column12: Improvements in the Manufacture of Boots, Shoes, or the like and in Soles thefefor.
column13: 10,104. Alonso Ú Yzaguire, F., and Villa, J. Y. July 10. Boot soles, making by stitching together coiled plaits.-In making " rope " soles for boots, shoes, slippers, &c. in which one or more bands are wound in known manner, pressed, and then sewn transversely by two threads 3,4, Fig. 1, the ends of the threads are secured at the toe and heel by first crossing or knotting them, as shown at 5, and then forcing them into the sole by means of barbed h o o k members 6 ; various forms of these, which may be made of iron, steel, wood, &c., are shown in Fig. 5. Preferably, one fastening- member is used at the toe, and three, arranged radially, at the heel. Where the ends of the threads 3, 4 are too short to be crossed or knotted, they are clamped by a separate thread or cord 7, Fig. 4, which is secured by two or more fastening- members. A separate cord may be secured by one or more members, and after insertion, the free ends of the cord and of the threads 3, 4 may be knotted together. In the case in which the upper is inserted between the two outer layers of the band and is secured by the threads 3, 4, the fastening-members 6 also serve to close the heel and toe portions of the upper. In other cases, the members are driven in sufficiently far to leave a clear space for securing the upper to the sole by edge-sewing. Figs. 6, 7, and 9 show a machine for use in the manufacture of these soles. After the ends of the threads 3, 4 have been crossed or knotted, the soles are placed in moulds 8, Fig. 9, and held at the toe and heel by pins 9 projecting from carriers 10. These carriers are linked together to form a conveyer, Fig. 7, which is fed intermittently by a pair of hookedended rods 42 adapted in their feeding movement to engage under a bevel 15, Fig. 9, on the end of each mould, and on their backward movement to slide over a bevel 14 on the upper face of the mould. The soles in turn are fed under a coverplate 43, Fig. 6, which prevents them from rising out of their moulds, and in this position the fastening-members, which are placed in grooves 13, Fig. 9, are driven into the sole by punches 51, Fig. 6, adjustably secured in holders 50 and operated from rods 46 pivoted to eccentrics mounted on shafts 29, 32.

column12: GENERATING THREE-DIMENSIONAL VIRTUAL TOURS FROM TWO-DIMENSIONAL IMAGES
column13: Interactive three-dimensional (3D) virtual tours are generated from ordinary two-dimensional (2D) still images such as photographs. Two or more 2D images are combined to form a 3D scene, which defines a relationship among the 2D images in 3D space. 3D pipes connect the 2D images with one another according to defined spatial relationships and for guiding virtual camera movement from one image to the next. A user can then take a 3D virtual tour by traversing images within the 3D scene, for example by moving from one image to another, either in response to user input or automatically. In various embodiments, some or all of the 2D images can be selectively distorted to enhance the 3D effect, and thereby reinforce the impression that the user is moving within a 3D space. Transitions from one image to the next can take place automatically without requiring explicit user interaction.

column12: PROCEDURE FOR OBTAINING AN INHIBITOR DERIVED FROM SUNFLOWER OIL FOR THE POLYDUCTS CORROSION.
column13: The present disclosure is related to the procedure for obtaining a corrosion inhibitor for polyducts based on three main stages: (1) elaborating the imidazoline; (2) preparing the asset (carboxy-imidazoline), and (3) formulating the asset (carboxy-imidazoline). The first stage corresponds to obtaining the imidazoline precursor derived from sunflower oil and EDTA. The second stage consists of modifying of imidazoline to obtain the asset (carboxy-imidazoline). Finally, the third stage consists of formulating of the asset with xylenes and isopropyl alcohol to obtain the corrosion inhibitor for the polyducts. In this regard, it should be noted that the improvement of the present procedure lies in reducing the manufacturing time, maintaining the quality and efficiency of the inhibitor, with which, the final product will be obtained at a lower cost. During the process of the present invention, the reduction of the manufacturing time is likely to be carried out in: the manufacturing stage of the imidazoline; the preparation stage of the asset (carboxy-imidazoline); the reaction period for obtaining the asset; the cooling procedure of each stage of the synthesis; the addition of xylenes at a temperature of around 110°C after the obtaining stage of the imidazoline; the addition of xylenes at a temperature of around 110°C after the obtaining stage of the carboxy-imidazoline; the addition of xylenes at temperatures between 60 and 110°C during the formulation stage of the corrosion inhibitor; and the addition of isopropyl alcohol at a temperature of 55°C during the formulation stage of the corrosion inhibitor. With the improvement that this procedure represents , the collection time has been reduced up to 11 hours, maintaining the quality and protection efficiency based on the NACE TM-0172 and NACE ID182 methods, the latter, both in bitter (H2S) and sweet (CO2) media. The results obtained in the industrial scaling of this corrosion inhibitor, makes the product competitive at commercial level and with application perspectives both in Mexico and in other countries.

column12: PROCESSES FOR THE PREPARATION OF PANCRATISTATIN AND PANCRATISTATIN ANALOGUES
column13: Processes for the preparation of pancratistatin and pancratistatin analogues. The key step is the reaction of a 1,3-dioxan-5-one and a nitroolefine in the presence of an amine. The process may take place in an enantioselective way when a chiral amine is used. Reduction processes then give new and advanced intermediates that are useful for the preparation of pancratistatin or selected pancratistatin analogues. The reported process also provides a method for the efficient synthesis of nitroenals, starting materials of the synthesis. Analogues of pancratistatin are also provided.

column12: FREEFORM PANELLING SYSTEM WITH HIGH ENERGY EFFICIENCY
column13: The invention concerns a freeform panelling system with high energy efficiency comprising a plurality of panels (1) connected to each other by means of a connection (2). Each panel (1) comprises two enveloping sheets (3) and (4), one being an inner sheet (3) and the other an outer sheet (4), composed of an SiO 2 -PMMA resin matrix reinforced with natural cellulose nanofibres and an intermediate vacuum chamber (5) of 1hPa, disposed between the inner sheet (3) and the outer sheet (4) and filled with a monolithic silica aerogel. The means for connecting the panels have an undercut (9) in two of the first contiguous edges (10, 11) of the panel in a first corner of the panel and a step (12) of a thickness equal to that of the undercut (9) in the two contiguous edges (13, 14) in the second corner opposite the first corner.

column12: SYNTHESIS OF POLYOXYGENATED NITROGEN SYSTEMS, COMPRISING REACTIONS BETWEEN ENAMINES OF 1,3-DIOXAN-5-ONES AND NITROOLEFINS
column13: The invention relates to the synthesis of polyoxygenated nitrogen systems, comprising reactions between enamines of 1,3-dioxan-5-ones and nitroolefins. More specifically, the invention relates to the reaction between enamines having formula II which are derived from 1,3-dioxan-5-ones I and nitroolefins having formula III. In this way, novel polyoxygenated nitrogen systems are generated having formula IV and V, which, as they are or following simple transformations, constitute synthetic intermediates and/or analogues of different systems of proven biological/pharmacological interest, such as certain antibiotics, or tetrodotoxin, pancratistatin or the analogues thereof. The aforementioned reactions involve the use of enamines II in Michael-type addition reactions and in direct annealing processes with double acceptor systems at relative positions 1, 3. Said N acceptors include nitroolefins III, wherein R = CHO (alphanitroenals). The invention also relates to the preparation thereof, which is based on the oxidation of the corresponding precursor alcohols VII, and the use of same in annealing processes.

column12: SYSTEM FOR AUTOMATICALLY CONTROLLING THE HIGH LIFT DEVICES OF AN AIRCRAFT DURING TAKEOFF
column13: A system for automatically controlling lift augmentation devices of an aircraft, during a phase of take-off by the aircraft, includes a controllable actuator that shifts the lift-augmentation devices, and a control unit for generating control demands to control the actuator to bring the lift-augmentation devices into a defined position. The control unit further includes a detector that detects actual take-off by the air craft and, if appropriate, signals such detection to the control unit. At start of the take-off phase, the lift-augmentation device are brought into a first position, in which they are deployed. The control unit generates, at least when the detector signals the actual take-off, a control demand making it possible to bring the lift-augmentation devices into a second position, in which the lift-augmentation devices are retracted by comparison with the first position.
column15: CHATRENET DOMINIQUE;;CART-LAMY MARTINE;;ALONSO FERNANDO;;MATHIEU GERARD

column12: VOLATILE SUBSTANCE EVAPORATOR DEVICE
column13: The volatile substance-evaporator device comprises a source of heat (1) and a refill (2) that includes said volatile substances, and is characterized in that said source of heat is a flame (1) that heats a transmission element+ (3), which heats said refill (2) in order to evaporate the volatile substances. The result thereof is that the volatile substances evaporate properly, without the need to use batteries or a similar power source, simply by the use of a flame, for example in the form of a candle, the financial cost thereof being very low.

column13:
System for automatically controlling lift-augmentation devices of an aircraft during take-off. 

    The control system ( 1 A) includes actuating means ( 15 ) for shifting the lift-augmentation devices, a control unit ( 16 A) for controlling the actuating means ( 15 ), and a means ( 17 ) for detecting the actual take-off by the aircraft. At the start of the take-off phase, the lift-augmentation devices are brought into a first position, in which they are deployed, and said control unit ( 16 A) is formed in such a way as, at least when said means ( 17 ) signals the actual take-off, to generate a control demand making it possible to bring the lift-augmentation devices into a second position, which they are retracted by comparison with the first position.

column12: PROCESS FOR GRINDING NOBLE METALS IN LIQUID MEDIUM
column13: The process comprises a) introducing the noble metal in the form of sheets, foils or wafers inside a container provided with grinding means; b) adding into said container a liquid medium having a density comprised between 0.61 and 1,50 g/ml at room temperature; c) grinding the noble metal in the presence of said liquid medium until the noble metal is transformed into a product comprised of noble metal particles of the desired size; d) allowing said particles to sediment; e) extracting said liquid medium; and f) removing the noble metal transformed into fine particles having an average size comprised between 0.00020 mm2 and 0.6mm2, and totally dry. These particles can be added to a liquid medium such as perfume, essence, sparkling wine, champagne, liquor, edible oil, paint or the like.

CASCO NEUMATICO PARA MASAJE Y ESTIMULACION DEL RIEGO SANGUINEO EN LA CABEZA, QUE SE HALLA CONSTITUIDO POR DOS SECCIONES O CAMARAS, UNA EXTERIOR Y OTRA INTERIOR, DE MODO QUE LA CAMARA EXTERIOR CUBRE TODO EL CUELLO CABELLUDO, SIENDO ELASTICA EN LAS ZONAS PERIMETRALES A FIN DE ADAPTARSE A LA FRENTE, PATILLAS Y NUCA, LA CUAL SE PUEDE INFLAR O DESINFLAR MEDIANTE UNA PERA, MIENTRAS QUE LA CAMARA INTERIOR SE HALLA INSTALADA ENTRE LA PARTE INTERIOR DE LA CAMARA EXTERIOR Y EL CUERO CABELLUDO, ESTANDO FORMADA POR PEQUEÑAS BURBUJAS HINCHABLES Y ADECUADAMENTE DISTRIBUIDAS, DE MANERA QUE CADA SERIE DE BURBUJAS ESTAN UNIDAS ENTRE SI PERMITIENDO SU INFLADO SIMULTANEO, A LA VEZ QUE ESTAN UNIDAS A UNA PEQUEÑA TUBERIA CONECTADA A UN DISTRIBUIDOR DE AIRE A PRESION ACCIONADO POR MOTOR QUE UTILIZA UN PEQUEÑO COMPRESOR, ESTANDO ESTOS ALIMENTADOS DIRECTAMENTE DE LA RED O DESDE UNA BATERIA.

column12: GENERATING A 3D INTERACTIVE IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE FROM A 2D STATIC IMAGE
column13: A two-dimensional (2D) static image may be used to generate a three- dimensional (3D) interactive immersive experience. An image type of the 2D image may first be identified. The image type may be selected from a set of types such as interior, exterior, people, corridor, landscape, and other. Each image type may have an associated main feature type. The main feature of the 2D image may be identified using the corresponding main feature type. Then, unless the 2D image is of the "other" image type, a 3D object with two or more planes may be generated. The planes may intersect on the identified main feature. A virtual camera may be positioned proximate the 3D object, and a 3D view of the 3D object may be generated and displayed for the user. The user may optionally move the virtual camera, within limits, to view the 3D object from other locations.

column12: VOLATILE SUBSTANCE-EVAPORATOR DEVICE
column13: The invention relates to a volatile substance evaporator device comprising a heat source (1) and a refill (2) including said volatile substances, and it is characterized in that said heat source is a flame (1) that heats a transmission element (3) which heats said refill (2) for evaporating the volatile substances. The result thereof is that the volatile substances evaporate properly without the need to use batteries or a similar power source, simply by the use of a flame, for example in the form of a candle, the financial cost thereof being very low.

column12: PROCEDIMIENTO PARA CALENTAR UN RECIPIENTE SENSIBLE A LA TEMPERATURA Y DISPOSITIVO DE CALENTAMIENTO CORRESPONDIENTE.
column13: Procedimiento para calentar un recipiente sensible a la temperatura y dispositivo de calentamiento correspondiente que consiste en efectuar un calentamiento de un recipiente (8) sensible a la temperatura, de manera tal que el aumento de temperatura sea gradual con el tiempo hasta alcanzar un valor predeterminado. El dispositivo de calentamiento (1, 1'') es una placa de cocina vitrocerámica (2) con elementos calentadores (3), un sistema de mando (4, 4''), para control de potencia de calentamiento de la placa (2). El procedimiento y el dispositivo son aplicables en el calentamiento de un recipiente en forma de olla o cazuela de material cerámico o arcilla, en donde al aumento de temperatura de dicho recipiente (8) se efectúa de forma gradual en el tiempo, con el fin de evitar los clásicos cambios bruscos de temperatura que se producen mediante los sistemas actuales de calentamiento que, en ocasiones, producen la rotura, del recipiente.

column12: MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING WITH PRIOR KNOWLEDGE AND OVERSAMPLING
column13: The invention provides a method for performing magnetic resonance imaging, MRI, which exploits prior knowledge of the interactions between electromagnetic fields and spins in the sampled object. This technique is able to provide shorter acquisition times with respect to traditional (Nyquist-Shannon limited) MRI. The method is based on an encoding matrix formalism constructed from the specific knowledge of how every spin would evolve in time depending on their position for a given pulse sequence. This particular previous knowledge has not been fully exploited previously by traditional MRI techniques. Moreover, the method of the invention can be used in combination with other schemes, such as compressed sensing, parallel imaging, or deep learning, for further shortening the MRI scan time.

column12: 3D rotational presentation generated from 2D static images
column13: A computer-implemented method may be used to generate a 3D interactive presentation, referred to as a rotograph, illustrating a main object from a rotating viewpoint. A plurality of two-dimensional images may be received. A three-dimensional scene may be generated, with a virtual camera and an axis of rotation. Each of the two-dimensional images may be positioned in the three dimensional scene such that the plurality of two-dimensional images are oriented at different orientations about the axis of rotation. A motion pathway may be defined within the three-dimensional scene, by which the virtual camera is rotatable about the axis of rotation to view the plurality of two-dimensional images in sequence. A plurality of rotograph images may be captured with the virtual camera during motion of the virtual camera along the motion pathway to generate the rotograph, which may be displayed on a display screen.

column12: COMBUSTION GAS MIXING DEVICE THROUGH A SPEAR FOR PYROMETALLURGICAL PROCESS.
column13: The present disclosure is related to a device that allows processing and recovering waste resulting from fumes, dust, metals and other residual materials in the iron smelting processes, that uses a spear during the pyrometallurgical process, which is equipped with an arrow or nozzle, where gases are mixed during pyrometallurgical processes. The spear nozzle is designed in such a way, that the air that circulates outside of the same accelerates when traveling through the Venturi channels, which are machined in certain specific points of the nozzle.

column12: PROCESS FOR GRINDING NOBLE METALS IN LIQUID MEDIUM
column13: The process comprises: a) introduction of the precious metals, in the form of laminas, leafs or wafers in a container provided with grinding means; b) addition to said container with the precious metal of a liquid medium of a density between 0.61 g/ml and 1.50 g/ml at room temperature; c) grinding of the precious metal in the container, in the presence of the liquid medium, until the former is transformed into a product consisting of precious metal particles of the desired size; d) allowing said particles to sediment; e) extraction of the liquid medium; and f) removal of the precious metal transformed into fine particles with an average size between 0.00020 mm- and 0.6 mm 2 , completely dry. These particles can be added to a liquid medium such as a perfume, an essence, cava, champagne, liquor, edible oil, paint or the like.
column15: ALONSO VAREA JOSE FERNANDO-FEY;;BENITO DE VALLE JESUS VICARIO-

column12: CUTTING EDGE FOR MANUALLY ACTUATED KNIFE BLADE
column13: The invention relates to a cutting edge for a manually actuated knife blade which, applied to the blade (2) of a manual knife (3), preferably applied with a hollowing angle (a) having an inclination of 5º to 50º only on one side of the blade, defines a undulated line made up of recessed peaks (10) and projecting troughs (11) wherein said troughs (11) are always rounded, smooth and free of angles or vertices. Said undulated line of the cutting edge (1) has a waveshape which is generated from geometric shapes that may or may not belong to a guide line (12) defining the peaks (10) and troughs (11); said guide (12) is a straight or curved line or a combination of both, which indicates the axis of the generated waveshape and the direction followed by the line of the cutting edge (1) which may or may not coincide with the edge of the blade (2) on which the cutting edge (1) is implemented.

column12: PROCESS FOR GRINDING NOBLE METALS IN LIQUID MEDIUM
column13: The process comprises: a) introduction of the precious metals, in the form of laminas, leafs or wafers in a container provided with grinding means; b) addition to said container with the precious metal of a liquid medium of a density between 0.61 g/ml and 1.50 g/ml at room temperature; c) grinding of the precious metal in the container, in the presence of the liquid medium, until the former is transformed into a product consisting of precious metal particles of the desired size; d) allowing said particles to sediment; e) extraction of the liquid medium; and f) removal of the precious metal transformed into fine particles with an average size between 0.00020 mm- and 0.6 mm<2>, completely dry. These particles can be added to a liquid medium such as a perfume, an essence, cava, champagne, liquor, edible oil, paint or the like.

column12: System for lubrication of pressure of engine of motor vehicle, has hopper with outlet provided with local enlargement unit so as to promote venting of hopper and emptying of system, where hopper is designed as cylindrical bore
column13: The system has bearings provided with a machined semi-cylindrical surface (3), and an input hopper (10) formed into the cylindrical surface by oil in a cylindrical orifice. An outlet of the hopper has a local enlargement unit so as to promote venting of the hopper and emptying of the system. The hopper is designed as a cylindrical bore machined in a cylinder block (1), and the local enlargement unit is formed as a chamfer (13) of the outlet of the hopper, where the chamfer is designed as a conical chamfer.

column12: GENERATING A 3D INTERACTIVE IMMERSIVE EXPERIENCE FROM A 2D STATIC IMAGE
column13: A two-dimensional (2D) static image may be used to generate a three- dimensional (3D) interactive immersive experience. An image type of the 2D image may first be identified. The image type may be selected from a set of types such as interior, exterior, people, corridor, landscape, and other. Each image type may have an associated main feature type. The main feature of the 2D image may be identified using the corresponding main feature type. Then, unless the 2D image is of the "other" image type, a 3D object with two or more planes may be generated. The planes may intersect on the identified main feature. A virtual camera may be positioned proximate the 3D object, and a 3D view of the 3D object may be generated and displayed for the user. The user may optionally move the virtual camera, within limits, to view the 3D object from other locations.

column12: Dispositivo para el suministro de un producto en la taza de un inodoro
column13: El dispositivo para el suministro de un producto al interior de la taza de un inodoro, que comprende un elemento de sujeción (1) para su acoplamiento a la taza de un inodoro y un depósito recambiable (2) de dicho producto que puede colocarse en el exterior de la taza del inodoro, y se caracteriza porque también comprende un elemento absorbente (3) conectado con dicho depósito recambiable (2) e impregnado con dicho producto, pudiéndose colocar dicho elemento absorbente (3) en el interior de la taza del inodoro. Permite que todos sus componentes, y sobre todo los más susceptibles a ser manipulados, estén en todo momento lo más limpios posibles, suministrando el producto de una manera muy económica.

column12: MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING WITH PRIOR KNOWLEDGE AND OVERSAMPLING
column13: The invention provides a method for performing magnetic resonance imaging, MRI, which exploits prior knowledge of the interactions between electromagnetic fields and spins in the sampled object. This technique is able to provide shorter acquisition times with respect to traditional (Nyquist-Shannon limited) MRI. The method is based on an encoding matrix formalism constructed from the specific knowledge of how every spin would evolve in time depending on their position for a given pulse sequence. This particular previous knowledge has not been fully exploited previously by traditional MRI techniques. Moreover, the method of the invention can be used in combination with other schemes, such as compressed sensing, parallel imaging, or deep learning, for further shortening the MRI scan time.

column12: 3D ROTATIONAL PRESENTATION GENERATED FROM 2D STATIC IMAGES
column13: A computer-implemented method may be used to generate a 3D interactive presentation, referred to as a rotograph, illustrating a main object from a rotating viewpoint. A plurality of two-dimensional images may be received. A three-dimensional scene may be generated, with a virtual camera and an axis of rotation. Each of the two-dimensional images may be positioned in the three dimensional scene such that the plurality of two- dimensional images are oriented at different orientations about the axis of rotation. A motion pathway may be defined within the three-dimensional scene, by which the virtual camera is rotatable about the axis of rotation to view the plurality of two-dimensional images in sequence. A plurality of rotograph images may be captured with the virtual camera during motion of the virtual camera along the motion pathway to generate the rotograph, which may be displayed on a display screen.

column12: Volatile substance-evaporator device

column12: Access and mobility policy control
column13: A method for access and mobility policy control in a communication network, the method being performed by a first policy control entity, a second policy control entity, a network exposure entity and an application server, the method comprises: receiving, at a first policy control entity from an application server or a network exposure entity, a request for an access and mobility policy for a user equipment, the request further containing an application identifier or packet flow descriptor to which the access and mobility policy is applicable; transmitting, from the first policy control entity to the second policy control entity, a request for PDU session information for the user equipment, the request containing an application identifier or packet flow descriptor, in particular wherein the PDU session information is an application start/stop event, an undercredit event, a credit reassignment event or a usage report; transmitting the requested PDU session information from the second policy control entity to the first policy control entity; an access and mobility policy is generated at the first policy control entity based on the received PDU session information.

column13: Pedal for motor vehicles with a safety mechanism for head-on collisions, pivotable around a shaft (2;2') attached to a support piece (10;10'), and the safety mechanism comprising means that release the shaft (2;2') in the event of a head-on collision as a result of the action of activation means (40;40'). The release means comprise a retention member (20;20') that, in normal operating conditions of the pedal (1;1'), is arranged inserted at least partly in the support piece (10;10'), retaining the rotation shaft (2;2') in the support piece (10;10'), and at least one guide surface in the support piece (10;10'), which guides the movement of the retention member (20;20') in relation to said support piece (10;10') in the event of a head-on collision in which the activation means (40;40') act on the retention member (20;20'), releasing the rotation shaft (2;2').

column12: PEDAL FOR MOTOR VEHICLES
column13: Pedal assemblies for motor vehicles. In one implementation a pedal is pivotable around a shaft that is releasably fixed in a housing of a support piece by a retention member. The retention member is moveable between a first position corresponding to a normal operating condition and a second position corresponding to a head-on collision condition. In the first position a first part of the retention member rests against and holds the rotating shaft in the fixed position within the housing of the support piece and a first surface of the retention member rests against a guide surface of the support piece. The retention member is releasable from the support piece upon a force being applied to it in the event of the head-on collision, the first surface of the retention member adapted to ride along the guide surface of the support piece to cause the retention member to move from the first position to the second position in a manner that causes the first part of the retention member to be moved away from the rotating shaft so that the rotating shaft is moveable within the housing.

column12: MULTI-SURFACE SELF-PROPELLED DISPLACEMENT DEVICE.
column13: The present invention relates to a multi-surface self-propelled displacement device which is capable of moving a person by a plurality of rotating means. Said rotating means are propelled by a power transmission system actuated by an electric motor and powered by a rechargeable and interchangeable energy storage system, and which allows moving on different surfaces. The user controls the multi-surface self-propelled displacement device via wireless, which communicates with the electronic control system assembled for performing the speed variation and direction changes of displacement. Finally, it possesses an optional mode wherein it allows coupling to a trailer hitch base, which enables the connection of a non-motorized loading vehicle for transporting an additional load, as well as with a removable and/or hinged handlebar, thereby serving as a fixing and supporting media in the maneuverability of the device.

column12: SYSTEM FOR EMITTING VOLATILE SUBSTANCE
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a system for emitting a volatile substance which can adjust air circulation in such a way that an aroma produced by the system is increased or decreased.SOLUTION: A system 1 emitting a volatile substance comprises a housing 2 containing a volatile substance within it, a ventilation surface 3 having a ventilation window and arranged within the housing 2 and an adjustment element 4 capable of being arranged in at least two mutually different positions, a first position where the air circulation is maximum and a second position where the air circulation is minimum. In the first position, the adjustment element 4 opens an additional ventilation opening, and, in the second position, the adjustment element closes the additional ventilation opening, so that the circulation of air is easily adjustable for increase or decrease of an aroma simply by rotating the adjustment element.

column12: Sistema de liberación de sustancias volátiles

column12: DERIVADOS DE FENIL-GUANIDINA
column13: Se provee derivados de fenil-guanidina para la inhibición de Rac1 que bloquean su interacción con factores de intercambio de guanosina (GEFs) que pertenecen a la familia DBL, como agentes para el tratamiento de tumores agresivos y/o resistentes, así como composiciones farmacéuticas que los comprenden, su uso en terapia y procesos para su preparación. Reivindicación 1: Un compuesto de fórmula (1) o una sal del mismo, o cualquiera de sus formas estereoisoméricas o una mezcla de las mismas, en donde: R¹ y R¹ están seleccionados independientemente del grupo que consiste en H, alquilo C₁₋₄, CF₃, F, Cl, Br, I, -CN, OH, NH₂, -OCH₃, y NO₂; con la condición de que al menos uno de R¹ y R¹ son distintos de H; A es un radical seleccionado de alquilo C₁₋₆ lineal o ramificado o uno de un sistema conocido de anillos carbocíclico o heterocíclico con 1 - 2 anillos, en donde cada uno de los anillos que forman el sistema de anillos tiene 5 - 7 miembros, cada miembro independientemente seleccionado de C, N, O, S, CH, CH₂, NH; es saturado, parcialmente insaturado o aromático; estando A sustituido por uno o más radicales seleccionados del grupo que consiste en H, halógeno, nitro, ciano, alquilo C₁₋₆ lineal o ramificado, haloalquilo C₁₋₆, alquenilo C₂₋₆ lineal o ramificado, -OR², -COR², -COOR², -OC(O)R², -C(O)NR³R⁴, -NR³R⁴, -R⁵NHR⁶, -SR², -SO-R², -SO₂-R², y -SO₂NR³R⁴; en donde cada R² representa independientemente H o alquilo C₁₋₄ lineal o ramificado; cada R³ representa independientemente H o alquilo C₁₋₄ lineal o ramificado; cada R⁴ representa independientemente H, alquilo C₁₋₆ lineal o ramificado, fenilo, piridina o quinolina; en donde el sistema de anillo fenilo, piridina y quinolina está sustituido por uno o más radicales seleccionados de H, alquilo C₁₋₄ lineal o ramificado, y NH₂; R⁵ y R⁶ están independientemente seleccionados de H, alquilo C₁₋₄ lineal o ramificado; para uso en el tratamiento de una afección mediada por proteínas celulares Rho-GTPasa.

column12: PHENYL-GUANIDINE DERIVATIVES
column13: FIELD: chemistry.SUBSTANCE: invention relates to use of a compound of formula (I) or a pharmaceutically acceptable salt thereof, or any of stereoisomeric forms thereof, or mixtures thereof for treating pathological condition mediated by Rac1 cell proteins. In formula (I) Rand R' are independently selected from a group consisting of H and CF(provided that at least one of Rand R' is different from H); A is a carboxylic or heterocyclic ring system with one ring, where ring forming ring system, contains 5–7 members, where each member is independently selected from C, N and CH; or denotes an aromatic ring; wherein A substituted with one or more radicals selected from a group consisting of H, nitro, straight or branched (C-C)alkyl, halogen-(C-C)alkyl and -SONRR; where each Rindependently represents H or straight or branched (C-C)alkyl, each Rindependently represents H or straight or branched (C-C)alkyl. Invention also relates to a compound of formula (II), method for production thereof and pharmaceutical composition containing said compound. In formula (II) A is a carboxylic or heterocyclic ring system with one ring, where ring forming a ring system contains 5–7 members, where each member is independently selected from C, N and CH; or denotes an aromatic ring.EFFECT: disclosed compounds can be used as agents for treating fast-growing and/or resistant tumours.14 cl, 9 dwg, 3 tbl, 7 ex(I)(II)

column12: Sculpt transfer
column13: Embodiments provide for sculpt transfer. Embodiments include identifying a source polygon of a source mesh that corresponds to a target polygon of a target mesh. Embodiments include determining a first matrix defining a first rotation that aligns a target rest state of the target polygon to a source rest state of the source polygon, determining a second matrix defining a linear transformation that aligns the source rest state to a source pose of the source polygon, wherein the linear transformation comprises rotating and stretching, determining a third matrix defining a second rotation that aligns the source pose to the target rest state, and determining a fourth matrix defining a third rotation that aligns the source rest state to the source pose. Embodiments include determining a target pose of the target polygon based on the target rest state, the first matrix, the second matrix, the third matrix, and the fourth matrix.

column12: System for delivering volatile substances
column13: A system for delivering volatile substances comprising a housing inside which a volatile substance is housed; a ventilation surface placed in the housing provided with ventilation windows, and a regulating element that can be placed in at least two different positions: a first position of maximum air circulation, and a second position of minimum air circulation; and where the regulating element is further characterized in that in the first position, the regulating element opens an additional ventilation opening, and in the second position, the regulating element closes the of additional ventilation opening. The system for delivering volatile substances permits easy regulation of the circulation of air for increasing or decreasing a volatile substance, for example a fragrance, by simply rotating the regulating element.

column12: METODO PARA DETECTAR CELULAS DE MELANOMA
column13: Se describe un método altamente sensible y específico para monitorear la presencia de células cancerosas de melanoma, utilizando transcripcion reversa seguida de una doble ronda de reaccion en cadena de la polimerasa (RT-PCR) de una secuencia particular del marcador de estirpe melánica tirosinasa mediante el uso de nuevos pares de cebadores externos e internos, sentido y antisentido específicamente disenados. Se describe un kit para el uso de la deteccion de células de melanoma en una muestra biologica. Las muestras de sangre son examinadas al inicio y durante la aplicacion de un tratamiento anticáncer.

column13: The device includes a replaceable reservoir ( 1 ) of a product, and a predetermined quantity of the product is supplied to an interior of a toilet bowl. column12: Poste de reemplazo temporal de fácil manipulación y transporte
column13: Resumen Se revela un poste de remplazo temporal que consta de (i) una estructura tubular seccionada, que está constituida por una serie de segmentos y un sistema de tensión interna que se extiende a lo largo de todos los segmentos (ii) una base que permite que la estructura tubular se fije al terreno, (iii) una cruceta instalada de forma perpendicular a la estructura tubular seccionada, y que comprende una serie de aisladores, y (iv) unos medios de anclaje de la estructura contra el terreno, en donde la estructura tubular seccionada consta de un extremo inferior que se acopla a la base, un extremo superior que se une a la cruceta y un collarín que permiten la unión de la estructura tubular seccionada con los medios de anclaje, y donde tal dispositivo permite el remplazo provisional de un poste de la red eléctrica que ha colapsado, mientras se instala un poste definitivo, minimizando los tiempos en que se restablece el servicio de energía y por ende disminuyendo las pérdidas para la compañía distribuidora y las inconformidades de los usuarios finales como consecuencia de la afectación de la calidad del servicio.

column12: DEVICE FOR SUPPLYING A PRODUCT INSIDE A TOILET BOWL
column13: The invention relates to a device comprising a refillable store (1) for a product and dosing means (2) connected to said refillable store (1) for supplying a pre-determined quantity of said product inside the toilet bowl. Said dosing means (2) advantageously comprise: a first housing (3) and a second housing (4) which intercommunicate with each other, said first housing (3) being connected to said refillable store (1) and the water from the flushing of the toilet mixing with said product in said second housing (4); and a valve (5) that can be moved between two positions: a position for closing the communication between said first and second housings (3, 4), and a position for opening the communication between said first and second housings (3, 4). It allows the dosage, inside the toilet bowl, of a pre-determined quantity of product mixed with the water from the flushing of the toilet.

column12: CATALYST FOR THE HYDRODESULFURIZATION OF RESIDUES AND HEAVY CRUDES.
column13: The present invention is related to a catalyst mainly used in the second stage of a process for hydrotreating residues and heavy crudes, mainly for performing a hydrodesulfurization reaction. The catalyst of the present invention comprises at least an hydrogenation metal from Group VIB in an oxide form, a promoter from Group VIII also in an oxide form that is deposited over a catalytically active inorganic mixed oxide, this promoter mainly including alumina in the gamma phase and titanium. The present invention provides two processes for the synthesis of the product: the first process is performed from a commercial bohemite, which is peptized with an inorganic acid, and subsequently extruded, calcined and impregnated with a solution containing titanium so as to obtain a titanium/alumina (TiO2/Al2O3) support; the second process includes a commercial bohemite mechanically mixed with a titanium solution, which is peptized with an inorganic acid, and subsequently extruded and calcined for obtaining the aforementioned titanium/alumina (TiO2/Al2O3) support, where the active phases and the promoter are deposited. The metallic oxides are converted into sulfurs so as to maintain the catalyst active. The activation is carried out by a process for hydrosulfuring oxides forming the catalyst. The catalysts synthesized by the aforesaid processes besides being useful for substantially improving the hydrodesulfurization activity, are not quickly deactivated due to the poisoning of the pollutants present in the heavy crude loads, mainly metals such as nickel and vanadium (Ni and V).

column12: Catalyst for the hydrodesulfurization of residua and heavy crudes
column13: A catalyst for hydrotreating, especially hydrodesulfurization, of residua and heavy crudes is prepared by synthesizing the support from titanium and boehmite, to form either a titanium/alumina support (TiO 2 /Al 2 O 3 ) or a titanium-alumina support (TiO 2 —Al 2 O 3 ) that is thereafter provided with at least one hydrogenating metal from group VIB in oxide form and a promoter from group VIII also in oxide form. The (TiO 2 /Al 2 O 3 ) support is prepared from boehmite, which is peptized by using an inorganic acid, then extruded, calcined and impregnated with a solution containing titanium, while the (TiO 2 —Al 2 O 3 ) support is prepared by admixing boehmite with a titanium-containing solution, peptized using an inorganic acid, extruded and calcined to obtain the titanium-alumina support.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR AN OVERSAMPLED DATA CONVERTER
column13: According to one embodiment, a circuit includes a first oscillator having an oscillation frequency dependent on the input signal of a first input. The first oscillator is configured to oscillate when an enable input is in a first state and to maintain its phase or reduce its frequency when the enable input is in a second state. The circuit also includes a first time-to-digital converter having an input coupled to the output of the first oscillator, a pulse generator having an input coupled to the first clock input of the circuit and an output coupled to the enable input of the first oscillator. A pulse generator is configured to generate a pulse having a pulse width less than the duration of the clock signal of the first clock input.

column12: SISTEMA RECONFIGURABLE DE PROCESAMIENTO DE IMAGENES EN TIEMPO REAL PARA AYUDA A PACIENTES CON BAJA VISION.
column13: Se propone una plataforma única de ayuda a pacientes con baja visión. Se trata de obtener una plataforma de bajo coste, portátil, útil para diversas patologías al mismo tiempo, que pueda ser adaptable a las necesidades de diferentes pacientes, y que se pueda adaptar a la evolución en el tiempo de la capacidad visual del paciente. La plataforma completa de ayuda a la baja visión consiste en un sistema de adquisición de imágenes (cámara), un dispositivo de procesamiento de imágenes en tiempo real configurable (FPGA) y un visor portátil (HMD- Head Mounted Display).

column12: Extract from the carob pulp with lipid-lowering properties and procedure for obtaining it (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Extract from carob pulp and containing 15-30% condensed tannins, between 25-50% of lignin, between 10-20% of sugars, between 2-5% of fiber and proteins and less than one 10% humidity this composition gives lipid-lowering properties, lowering cholesterol and triglyceride levels, and can be used as a food supplement, as a nutraceutical or as an active ingredient with pharmaceutical characteristics. The obtaining procedure is based on the crushing of the locust bean pulp without seeds, later a wash in water to extract the majority of the present sugars, later filtering and extraction by means of a solution of water, acetone: water or ethanol: water. Finally the liquid extract is concentrated, eliminating the water by evaporation, crushing the obtained product to a suitable size. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: SELECTIVE SULFATE ANION DETECTION USING GUANYLATED FLUOROPHORES
column13: The present invention relates to the use of a guanylated fluorphore as a sulfate sensor and more in particular it relates to a method for selectively detecting and, optionally, quantifying sulfate anions in an aqueous sample by fluorescence spectroscopy using a guanylated fluorophore comprising a fluorescent group, containing a substituted or unsubstituted planar fluorescent core, and a guanidinyl moiety. The present invention also relates to a guanylated fluorophore comprising a fluorescent group and a guanidinyl moiety, wherein the fluorescent group is a fluorenyl group and the guanidinyl moiety is an alkyl substituted guanidinyl group. The present invention also relates to method for preparing such a guanylated fluorophore.

column12: Synthesis of Polyoxygenated Nitrogen Systems, Comprising Reactions Between Enamines of 1,3-Dioxan-5-Ones and Nitroolefins
column13: The invention relates to the synthesis of polyoxygenated nitrogen systems, comprising reactions between enamines of 1,3-dioxan-5-ones and nitroolefins. More specifically, the invention relates to the reaction between enamines having formula II which are derived from 1,3-dioxan-5-ones I and nitroolefins having formula III. In this way, novel polyoxygenated nitrogen systems are generated having formula IV and V, which, as they are or following simple transformations, constitute synthetic intermediates and/or analogues of different systems of proven biological/pharmacological interest, such as certain antibiotics, or tetrodotoxin, pancratistatin or the analogues thereof. The aforementioned reactions involve the use of enamines II in Michael-type addition reactions and in direct annealing processes with double acceptor systems at relative positions 1, 3. Said N acceptors include nitroolefins III, wherein R═CHO (alphanitroenals). The invention also relates to the preparation thereof, which is based on the oxidation of the corresponding precursor alcohols VII, and the use of same in annealing processes.

column12: RECONFIGURABLE, REAL-TIME IMAGE-PROCESSING DEVICE FOR ASSISTING PATIENTS WITH LOW VISION
column13: The invention relates to a reconfigurable, real-time image-processing device for assisting patients with low vision. The inventive device consists of a portable multitasking platform for assisting patients with low vision or visual impairments, comprising a set of image processing operations (digital zoom, edge enhancement and multiplexing of edges with the original image). More specifically, the invention relates to a low-cost, portable platform which can be used simultaneously for different pathologies, which can be adapted to the requirements of different patients and which, for degenerative pathologies, can adapt to changes over time in the visual capacity of the patient. The inventive platform contains an image-acquisition system, a reconfigurable circuit for the real-time processing of images (Field Programmable Gates Array, FPGA), a user interface and a viewer which emits the processed image.

column12: SELECTIVE SULFATE ANION DETECTION USING GUANYLATED FLUOROPHORES
column13: The present invention relates to the use of a guanylated fluorphore as a sulfate sensor and more in particular it relates to a method for selectively detecting and, optionally, quantifying sulfate anions in an aqueous sample by fluorescence spectroscopy using a guanylated fluorophore comprising a fluorescent group, containing a substituted or unsubstituted planar fluorescent core, and a guanidinyl moiety. The present invention also relates to a guanylated fluorophore comprising a fluorescent group and a guanidinyl moiety, wherein the fluorescent group is a fluorenyl group and the guanidinyl moiety is selected from an unsubstituted guanidinyl group, an alkyl substituted guanidinyl group and an aryl substituted guanidinyl group. The present invention also relates to method for preparing such a guanylated fluorophore.

column12: MECANISMO DE ENCAMINAMIENTO TOLERANTE A FALLOS ALTAMENTE ESCALABLE.
column13: Mecanismo de encaminamiento tolerante a fallos altamente escalable denominado S-Immunet, que se caracteriza por ser un mecanismo eficiente para tolerar fallos en redes de interconexión de computadores paralelos y distribuidos. El mecanismo está basado, por un lado, en un método de reencaminar los mensajes cuando se produce un fallo en la red y por otro lado, en una estructura hardware específica del aparato encaminador de mensajes. Las principales diferencias con los mecanismos previos de tolerancia a fallos son que la invención puede ser aplicada a redes muy grandes (miles de nodos) de tipo k-ary n-cube; no produce una sobrecarga de la red en ausencia de fallo; reconfiguración automática y transparente a la aplicación; reparados los componentes se recupera el rendimiento de la red antes del fallo y el nuevo mecanismo además es capaz de tolerar cualquier número de fallos de enlace y cualquier combinación espacial y temporal de fallos.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR ACQUIRING IMAGES OF AN OBJECT BY MEANS OF MAGNETIC RESONANCE, USING TIME-VARIABLE INHOMOGENEOUS MAGNETIC FIELDS
column13: The present invention relates to a method and to an apparatus for acquiring images of an object by means of magnetic resonance, using time-variable inhomogeneous magnetic fields, designed to: (a) generate a plurality of time-variable inhomogeneous gradient magnetic fields on a region of interest, producing a spatial codification of the magnetisation of the nuclear spins of the object; (b) apply a plurality of radio-frequency radiation pulse sequences, generating magnetic resonance signals; (c) detecting, demodulate and store the magnetic resonance signals generated, completing a first magnetic resonance scan; (d) repeat steps (a)-(c), carrying out one or more enhancement scans; and (e) reconstruct the spectra of the magnetic resonance signals emitted by the cores of the object and one or more images of same.

column12: APPARATUS FOR ARRANGING THE PLASTIC FOR COVERING GREENHOUSES
column13: Apparatus for arranging the plastic for covering greenhouses. The invention aims to mechanize in a safe manner the work involved in arranging the plastic film for covering greenhouses. The invention comprises the coordinated use of two components, a platform and a changing apparatus. The platform is provided with a reeling/unfolding system able to supply plastic film to the changing apparatus arranged on the roof, allowing the latter to be used not only for performing film-stretching operations but also for performing subsequent operations involving tensioning and fixing to the support structure. The platform is composed of a double rectangular frame (1) which is linearly hinged in its central zone by means of extendable bars with a locking mechanism (2). The base structure has, connected thereto, a bottom reeling winch (10), a top reeling/unfolding winch (5) and, on both sides, fixed stairs (6), hoists (7) and the corresponding safety rails (8/9). The changing apparatus is composed of a double curved gantry (11) linked by means of a stairway (12) and resting on pairs of rolling wheels (14).

column12: CONTROL DEL NIVEL DE OXIGENO Y AGUA EN LOS DISOLVENTES DE EXTRACCION SUPERCRITICA.
column13: CONTROL DEL NIVEL DE OXIGENO Y AGUA EN LOS DISOLVENTES DE EXTRACCION SUPERCRITICA. LA ESC APLICADA A LA OBTENCION DE PRODUCTOS DE BAJA O MODERADA SOLUBILIDAD, SUPONE EL OPERAR CON UNA CANTIDAD ELEVADA DE DISOLVENTE POR UNIDAD DE SOLUTO EXTRAIDO. DURANTE EL PROCESO DE EXTRACCION EL SOLUTO SE ENCUENTRA BAJO EL EFECTO DE LAS IMPUREZAS QUE ACOMPAÑAN AL DISOLVENTE Y LLEGAN A REPRESENTAR UNA CANTIDAD IMPORTANTE. ESTAS IMPUREZAS PUEDEN REACCIONAR CON EL SOLUTO QUE SE ESTA EXTRAYENDO Y DETERIORAR ASI EL PRODUCTO QUE SE OBTIENE MEDIANTE ESTA TECNICA. EL DISOLVENTE, LAS IMPUREZAS Y EL SOLUTO SE ENCUENTRAN EN LA MISMA FASE POR LO QUE LA REACCION TRANSCURRE EN FASE HOMOGENEA SIN LIMITACIONES A LA DIFUSION. EN ESTA PATENTE SE PRESENTAN LOS EFECTOS DEL OXIGENO Y DEL AGUA QUE ACOMPAÑAN A LOS DISOLVENTES PARA ESC, SOBRE LOS PRODUCTOS NATURALES Y SE INDICA PROCEDIMIENTO PARA REALIZAR EL PROCESO DE ESC ELIMINANDO EL EFECTO QUE PRODUCEN.

column12: Policy control for redundant transmissions
column13: Disclosed herein is an SMF (106) that receives a session request message sent by a User Equipment, UE, (102), the session request message comprising a DNN and S-NSSAI pair; upon receiving the session request message, the SMF sends a policy creation message to a PCF (110), the policy creation message comprising one or more of i) a DNN and S-NSSAI pair from the session request message, ii) information indicating that a user plane of a PDU session for the DNN and S-NSSAI pair has redundancy capabilities, and iii) a PDU session for the DNN and S-NSSAI pair. And iii) subscription information for the UE indicating that a subscriber is allowed to have redundant transmissions. Also disclosed is a method in a PCF (108), the PCF receiving a policy control request, the policy control request comprising a UE identifier identifying a UE (102); upon receiving the policy control request, obtaining policy information associated with the UE (102) from a data store (112), where the policy information comprises a list of allowed services; determining whether any one of the allowed services requires a redundant transmission; for each allowed service requiring redundant transmission, exporting a URSP rule pair; and storing the derived URSP rule pair in a data store (112) in association with the UE identifier.

column13: Method of detecting gases by infrared absorption using solid state Fabry-Perot filters. column12: Supercritical oxidation system using a cooled-wall shell
column13: Supercritical oxidation system using a cooled-wall shell Provides low cost reactors 8 for high pressure oxidation systems because it is not necessary for the pressurized shell 15 to withstand the oxidizing environment and because the shell 15 is at a lower temperature than the oxidation process. For this the said shell 15 is cooled internally by its own feed 1 from the system or by a fluid which is external to the process, and therefore requires less thickness, the cooling in both cases having a pressure similar to that of the oxidation. The oxidation takes place within a reaction chamber 17 which does not require great mechanical strength because its walls are at similar internal and external pressures, the said chamber 17 being within the reactor 8. Within the reactor 8 there is also an internal heat exchanger 16 which increases the energy efficiency of the system.

column12: Control of oxygen and water levels in supercritical extraction solvents
column13: Control of oxygen and water levels in supercritical extraction solvents SCE applied to the acquisition of products of low or moderate solubility presumes operation with a large quantity of solvent per unit of solute extracted. During the extraction process the solute is affected by impurities which accompany the solvent and which amount to an appreciable quantity. These impurities can react with the solute which is being extracted and thus reduce the quality of the product obtained by this technique. The solvent, the impurities and the solute are present in the same phase, so that the reaction is carried out in a homogeneous phase without limitations on diffusion. The effects of oxygen and water accompanying SCE solvents on natural products are presented in this patent and a process for carrying out the SCE process eliminating the effect which these produce is indicated.

column12: CARBON CARRIER CATALYST FOR REMOVING METAL FROM HEAVY CRUDE OIL AND RESIDUAL OIL
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To remove a heavy metal and sulfur as impurities from heavy crude oil and residual oil, and in particular, make a catalyst for removing metals and sulfur from the heavy crude oil and residual oil.

SOLUTION: The catalyst for hydrogenation treatment of heavy crude oil and residual oil, in particular, for removing metals, and includes an extrusion molded carbon carrier. The carbon carrier is activated by steam, and has a pore structure having a total pore volume of 0.7-1.8 cc/g, wherein 20% or more of the pores have pore diameters of 200-2,000 Å, and the ratio of the pores having pore diameters of 380-900 Å to the pores having pore diameters 200-2,000 Å is 40% or more.

column12: Tire having wear indication means and a method of manufacturing the tire
column13: A pneumatic tire has a tread with at least one groove having a groove depth Dg extending from an initial tread surface to the base of the groove. The tread has at least one tread wear indicator having at least two different colored portions. The tread wear indicator is a strip inclined at an angle relative to the tread surface and extending to a depth Dr at least equivalent to the groove depth Dg. In manufacturing the tire, the tread wear indicator is applied to a splice cut edge of the tread rubber such that, after splicing the tread rubber, the tread wear indicator strip is located within the tread splice.

column12: pneu dotado de um meio de indicação de desgaste e método de fabricação do pneu
column13: PNEU DOTADO DE UM MEIO DE INDICAçãO DE DESGASTE E MéTODO DE FABRICAçãO DO PNEU. Um pneumático tem uma banda de rodagem com pelo menos um entalhe tendo uma profundidade de entalhe Dg que se estende a partir de uma superfície inicial de banda de rodagem para a base do entalhe. A banda de rodagem tem pelo menos um indicador de desgaste de banda de rodagem tendo pelo menos duas porções coloridas diferentes. O indicador de desgaste de banda de rodagem é uma tira inclinada em um ângulo com relação à superfície de banda de rodagem e que se estende para uma profundidade Dr pelo menos equivalente à profundidade de entalhe Dg. Na fabricação do pneu, o indicador de desgaste de banda de rodagem é aplicado a uma borda de corte de junta da borracha de banda de rodagem de tal modo que, após a junção da borracha de banda de rodagem, a tira indicadora de desgaste de banda de rodagem se localize dentro da junta de banda de rodagem.

column12: Catalysts compositions for the polymerization and copolymerization of alpha-olefins
column13: The invention relates to a polymerization catalyst system, a polymerization process using that catalyst system and polymers produced therefrom. The catalyst system results from the combination of a co-catalyst and a bridged 3-substituted-indenyl metallocenes of formula (I) wherein M is Ti, Zr or Hf, R 1  is an indenyl ligand; R 2  and R 3  bonded to R 1  at position 3 are, independently, H or a monovalent organic radical; R 2 ' and R 3'  bonded to R 1  at position 2 are, independently, hydrogen or a monovalent organic radical; wherein at least one of R 2  and R 3  is a monovalent organic radical; Q is a divalent group and X 1  and X 2  are monovalent ligands, its racemic or meso stereoisomers and mixtures thereof. Polymers made with said polymerization catalyst system can have from narrow to broad molecular weight distribution (MWD) or from narrow bimodal MWD to broad bimodal MWD and melt indexes from about 0 to about 25 without the need of using molecular weight regulators by properly selecting the indenyl substituent (size and number of substituents) and the form used (pure stereoisomers of mixtures thereof).

column12: Method for inspecting faults appearing in a composite carbon fibre material by perforation of the pocket during the production process
column13: The method involves removing pocket which surrounds a part after drying, and placing an infrared camera (102) and lamps (103) for heating a material through light pulse (109) in front of an infrared thermography test (101). The test is heated through the lamps, and the evolution of temperature of a surface of the specimen during its heating and cooling, is captured through the camera, where data is transferred to a computer (104). Presence of defects is determined by occurrence of contrast on thermogram in digital values, temperature values or in temperature contrast values.

column12: Sigma-Delta-Modulator für Sensoren
column13: Bei verschiedenen Ausführungsbeispielen wird eine Schaltung bereitgestellt. Die Schaltung beinhaltet: eine Spannungs-Biasing-Schaltung, die mit einem MEMS-Mikrofon-Sensor (MEMS: mikroelektromechanisches System) gekoppelt ist, wobei der MEMS-Mikrofon-Sensor mit einer Treiberschaltung gekoppelt ist und die Treiberschaltung mit einer oszillatorbasierten Analog-Digitäl-Wandlerschaltung gekoppelt ist. Die oszillatorbasierte Analog-Digital-Wandlerschaltung kann einen Sigma-Delta-Modulator N-ter Ordnung beinhalten, wobei N eine ganze Zahl größer oder gleich 1 ist.

column12: CATALYST COMPOSITION FOR POLYMERIZATION AND COPOLYMERIZATION OF ALPHA OLEFIN
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a catalyst system, a polymerization method using the catalyst system and a polymer produced by the method.

SOLUTION: The catalyst composition is obtained by combining a bridged indenyl metallocene represented by general formula I with an organoaluminum or perfluoroboron auxiliary catalyst. In general formula I, M indicates a transition metal atom of the group 4 of the Periodic Table of Elements; Q indicates a divalent substituent; and X1and X2indicate a monovalent anionic ligand. A polyethylene copolymer produced can have a narrow-broad unimodal or narrow-broad bimodal molecular weight distribution and a melt index of about 0 to 10 or more, without the need for a molecular weight regulator.
