column12: Sigma delta modulator for sensors
column13: The invention provides a sigma delta modulator for sensors. In various embodiments, a circuit is provided. The circuit includes: a voltage biasing circuit coupled to a microelectro-mechanical system (MEMS) microphone sensor, the MEMS microphone sensor coupled to a driver circuit, and the driver circuit coupled to an oscillator-based ADC circuit. The oscillator-based ADC circuit may include an Nthorder sigma-delta modulator, where N is an integer equal to or greater than 1.

column13:
MÉTODO DE EVOLUCIÓN Y CONTROL DE SUS DEFECTOS DE LOS CÁTODOS PERMANENTES Y LAS CELDAS ELECTROLÍTICAS, QUE PERMITE MEJORAR LA CALIDAD DELAS PLACAS DE METAL PRODUCIDA, MEDIANTE EL MANTENIMIENTO PREVENTIVO Y CORRECTIVO DE DICHOS DEFECTOS, QUE COMPRENDE LAS SIGUIENTES ETAPAS:

E) ANALIAZAR LOS DATOS IRGANIZADOS POR CELDA ELECREOLITICA PARA LA CONFECCION DE TENDENCIAS Y LA ESTIMACION DE VALORES FUTUROS;
F) ANALIZAR LOS DATOS ORGANIZADOS POR CÁTODO PERMANENTE PARA LA CONFECCIÓN DE TENDENCIAS Y LA ESTIMACIÓN DE VALORES FUTUROS; Y
G) UTILIZAR DICHAS ESTIMACIONES PARA PROGRAMAR LA REPARACIÓN DE LOS CÁTODOS PERMANENTES O CELDAS ELECTROLÍTICAS.

column12: Tire having wear indication means and a method of manufacturing the tire
column13: A pneumatic tire (10) has a tread (16) with at least one groove (18) having a groove depth (D G ) extending from an initial tread surface to the base of the groove. The tread has at least one tread wear indicator having at least two different colored portions. column13: A supported carbon having high surface area, high pore volume containing (i) molybdenum (ii) a metal of non noble Group VIII, (iii) phosphorous, is used for hydrometallization of heavy crude oil and residue. Long run activity studies show that catalyst having only molybdenum supported on activated carbon has good stability with time-on-stream and very high metal retention capacity.

column12: Katalysator for polymerisering og kopolymerisering av alfa-olenfiner
column13: Foreliggende oppfinnelse vedrører en metallocenforbindelse, et katalysatorsystem, en polymerisasjonsprosess som anvender katalysatorsystemet og polymerer fremstilt ved denne. Katalysatorsystemet er resultatet av en kombinasjon av broede indenyl metallocener some er beskrevet ved generell formel 1 og en organoaluminium eller bor perfluorert kokatalysator, hvor M er et overgangsmetall fra gruppe 4 i det periodiske system, Q er en divalent substituent og X1 og X2 er monovalente, anioniske ligander. Polyolefin-kopolymerene fremstilt med katalysatorene i henhold til oppfinnelsen kan ha fra bred til small bimodal til bred bimodal molekylvektsfordeling og smelteindekser fra ca. 0 til høyere enn 10, uten behov for molekylvektsregulatorer avhengig av passende valg av indenylsubstituenten, antallet substituenter (enkel eller begge indenene er substituert) og typen stereoisomer form som brukes: ren (racemisk eller meso) eller blandinger derav.

column12: PHOTOLUMINISCENT GEOPOLYMER.
column13: The present invention refers to an inorganic-material geopolymer having an amorphous to semi-crystalline structure with photoluminiscent properties. Said material, due to the optical properties thereof, is useful for the development and/or manufacture of photoluminiscent ceramic materials, mortar, concrete and composites, which may be applied in the industry in general, mainly in the signaling, traffic, electric, electro-mechanical, architectonic and decoration, construction, military, automotive, aeronautical, oil, and naval industries as well as alternative energy industries. The photoluminiscent geopolymer is characterised in that it is highly resistant to UV light unlike organic photoluminiscent polymers currently available on the market. In addition, the present invention is highly resistant to fire and has a highly resistant electric insulation as well as a high chemical resistance to diverse compounds and organic solvents. The inventive material acquires adhesive or binding pro perties at the moment of the manufacture thereof, therefore may be used as inorganic cement and may be adhered to metallic, ceramic, glass and composite surfaces. Once said photoluminiscent geopolymer is excited by a source of UV beams, it may emit, from the inner portion of the matrix thereof, light from about 12 hours which may change colour depending on the photoluminiscent crystal previously used. Another advantage of the present geopolymer is that it is obtained at room temperature or at temperatures lower than 300°C, thereby substantially reducing the production costs in the industry.

column12: EMPLEO DE SECUENCIAS PSEUDO-ORTOGONALES EN SISTEMAS PHASED ARRAY PARA EXPLORACION SIMULTANEA EN MULTIPLES DIRECCIONES
column13: Se propone el uso de las técnicas phased array con una excitación codificada a partir de un conjunto de secuencias pseudo-ortogonales, como por ejemplo las derivadas de secuencias pseudoaleatorias o de CSS (Complementary Sets of Sequences), así como su posterior etapa de proceso, todo lo cual permite obtener imágenes del entorno con elevada resolución a partir de una única emisión que simultáneamente abarca múltiples direcciones diferenciadas del entorno, a diferencia de los sistemas phased array clásicos que precisan de una emisión por cada sector a inspeccionar. Esta invención introduce un nuevo método de excitación de los elementos del array y post-procesamiento de los ecos recibidos que incrementa la velocidad de generación de imágenes, así como la distancia máxima a inspeccionar manteniendo la calidad de la imagen.

column12: MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING WITH ZERO ECHO TIME AND SLICE SELECTION
column13: The invention provides a novel radio frequency sequence, suitable for performing Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) of 2-dimensional (2D) slices (rather than 3- dimensional volumes) of samples exhibiting short magnetization coherence times (i.e. hard tissues). The SS-ZTE pulse sequence comprises the following steps: a) magnetizing all spins in the sample from a longitudinal direction to the transverse plane; b) exciting the 2D slice of interest, which comprises the selective locking of said 2D sample slice magnetization while spoiling the magnetization in the rest of sample volume; c) making the magnetization of the selected 2D slice impervious to reconfigurations of the magnetic field gradients from slice selection to encoding and readout; d) reading out of the free induction decay signal of the sample; e) repeating steps (a-d) with different readout directions, so as to gather a corresponding number of radial spokes of the plane defined by the 2D sample slice.

column12: OBTAINING MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGES WITH ZERO ECHO TIME AND SECTION SELECTION (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Zero echo time magnetic resonance imaging and section selection. The invention provides a novel radio frequency sequence, suitable for performing magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of two-dimensional (2D) sections (rather than three-dimensional volumes) of samples showing short magnetization coherence times (i.e., tissues hard). The SS-ZTE pulse sequence comprises the following steps: a) magnetizing all spins in the sample from a longitudinal direction to the transverse plane; b) exciting the 2D section of interest, which comprises selectively blocking said magnetization of the 2D sample section while offsetting the magnetization in the rest of the sample volume; c) rendering the magnetization of the selected 2D section immune to reconfigurations of magnetic field gradients from section selection to encoding and reading; d) reading the free induction decay signal from the sample; e) repeating steps (a-d) with different reading directions, to collect a corresponding number of radial rays from the plane defined by the 2D sample section. column12: MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING WITH ZERO ECHO TIME AND SLICE SELECTION
column13: A novel radio frequency sequence, suitable for performing Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) of 2-dimensional (2D) slices of samples exhibiting short magnetization coherence times (i.e., hard tissues). The SS-ZTE pulse sequence contains the following steps: a) magnetizing all spins in the sample from a longitudinal direction to the transverse plane; b) exciting the 2D slice of interest, which comprises the selective locking of said 2D sample slice magnetization while spoiling the magnetization in the rest of sample volume; c) making the magnetization of the selected 2D slice impervious to reconfigurations of the magnetic field gradients from slice selection to encoding and readout; d) reading out of the free induction decay signal of the sample; e) repeating steps (a-d) with different readout directions, so as to gather a corresponding number of radial spokes of the plane defined by the 2D sample slice.

column12: Method of inhibiting metastatic dissemination using desmopressin
column13: The present invention relates to the use of 1-deamino-8-D-arginine vasopressin (desmopressin), or a pharmaceutically acceptable salt thereof or a pharmaceutical composition containing any of them, in the preparation of a medication which minimizes metastatic dissemination during cancer surgery. Additionally, the invention also relates to pharmaceutical compositions comprising the same and to a method of treating a mammal in order to inhibit metastatic spread during surgical extirpation of a cancer mass.

column12: SENSORES DE PRESION DISTRIBUIDOS DE GRAN SUPERFICIE BASADOS EN POLITIOFENOS
column13: Sensores de presión distribuidos de gran superficie basados en politiofenos. La presente invención se refiere a sensores de presión distribuidos de gran superficie que comprenden al menos dos sustratos flexibles, estando recubierto al menos uno de ellos total o parcialmente por una capa de un politiofeno que contiene unidades estructurales repetitivas de fórmula (I), en la que R1 y R2 son independientemente un grupo alquilo C1-C12 o forman un grupo 1,n-alquileno C1-C12, siendo n = 1-12, opcionalmente sustituidos por un grupo alquilo C1-C12, alqueno C2-C12, vinileno, bencilo, fenilo, halógeno, o por un grupo funcional éster, amino, amido o éter opcionalmente sustituido por un grupo alquilo C1-C12; y uno o más espaciadores aislantes. Dichos sensores son flexibles y fáciles de fabricar y pueden presentar distintas configuraciones simétricas, simples o multicapa, según se desee.

column12: Coarse-fine quantization architecture for multiphase VCO-based ADCs
column13: An analog-to-digital converter includes a ring oscillator having an input for receiving an analog signal, a coarse Gray code counter having a first input coupled to a first output of the ring oscillator and a second input for receiving a clock signal, a fine counter having first inputs coupled to secondary outputs of the ring oscillator and a second input for receiving the clock signal, a first difference generator having an input coupled to the output of the coarse counter, a second difference generator having an input coupled to the output of the fine counter, and an adder having a first input coupled to the output of the first difference generator, a second input coupled to the output of the second difference generator, and an output for providing a digital signal corresponding to the analog signal.

column12: COMPOSITES TERMOPLASTICOS REFORZADOS ESTAMPABLES BASADOS EN POLICLORURO DE VINILO, PROCEDIMIENTO PARA SU OBTENCION Y TRANSFORMACION
column13: Composites termoplásticos reforzados estampables basados en policloruro de vinilo, procedimiento para su obtención y transformación. Los composites termoplásticos reforzados estampables (TRE) contienen (a) una resina de PVC constituida a su vez por dos resinas de PVC, una obtenida por polimerización en microsuspensión y la otra en suspensión, (b) un plastificante, (c) un agente de entrecruzamiento, (d) un sistema estabilizante térmico, (e) un catalizador de la reacción de entrecruzamiento del PVC, (f) un lubricante y (g) otras cargas. La obtención del composite comprende la dispersión de la resina de PVC en una mezcla previa de los aditivos y posterior adición de las cargas. Estos composites son adecuados para elaborar preimpregnados termoplásticos utilizando una máquina de elaborar preimpregnados termoestables de tipo compuesto moldeable en forma de hoja (SMC). Los materiales resultantes son útiles para fabricar piezas para el sector del transporte.

column12: Set of stampable reinforced PVC based thermoplastics consists of two PVC resins with plasticizer, catalyst, interweaving agent, thermal stabilizer and additives
column13: Imprintable reinforced thermoplastic composites based on vinyl polychloride, procedure for obtaining and processing them.The imprintable reinforced thermoplastic composites contain (a) a PVC resin itself made up of two PVC resins, one obtained by microsuspension polymerisation and the other in suspension, (b) a plasticiser, (c) a crossover agent, (d) a temperature stabilising system, (e) a catalyst for the PVC crossover reaction, (f) a lubricant and (g) other loads. The composite is obtained by dispersion of the PVC resin in a previous mixture of additives and later addition of the loads. These composites are suitable for elaborating thermoplastic pre-impregnations using a machine for elaborating thermoplastic pre-impregnations such as sheet moulded compounds (SMCs). The resulting materials can be used to produce parts for the transport sector.

column13: Infective clones and vectors derived from coronaviruses and their applications. The coronavirus-derived infective clone comprises a cDNA encoding the gRMA of a coronavirus cloned under a transcriptional promoter sequence. The recombinant viral vector comprises an infectious clone modified to contain a heterologous nucleic acid inserted into said infective clone under conditions that allow expression of said heterologous nucleic acid. Infective clones and vectors are useful in both basic and applied research, in the development of efficient expression systems for products of interest (proteins, enzymes, antibodies, etc.), vaccine vectors, and gene therapy. column13: The present invention relates to a compound having inhibitory activity on a Rho-GTPase cell protein, the compound having the formula I (Formula I) wherein A is selected from N and N—H, R 1 is selected from H and NHR 3 , R 2 is selected from NHR 4 , OR 4 , O and halogen, R 3 is selected from H and —COR 5 , R 4 is selected from H, a C 1 -C 6 alkyl and a substituted or unsubstituted phenyl, R 5 is selected from a C 1 -C 12 alkyl and a substituted or unsubstituted phenyl, R 6 is selected from H, —COR 5 , —CO 2 R 5 , —PR 7 R 8 and —PR 7 R 8 OPR 7 R 8 R 8 R 7 , R 7 is selected from O and S, R 8 is selected from H, OR 4 and OSATE (—OCH 2 CH 2 SCOR 5 ), and wherein each represents a single bond or a double bond, provided that when one of them is a double bond the other one is a single bond, and pharmaceutically acceptable salts and derivatives thereof. column12: CLONES Y VECTORES INFECTIVOS DERIVADOS DE CORONAVIRUS Y SUS APLICACIONES.
column13: Clones y vectores infectivos derivados de coronavirus y sus aplicaciones. El clon infectivo derivado de un coronavirus comprende un cDNA que codifica el gRMA de un coronavirus clonado bajo una secuencia promotora de la transcripción. El vector viral recombinante comprende un clon infectivo modificado para contener un ácido nucleico heterólogo insertado en dicho clon infectivo bajo condiciones que permiten la expresión de dicho ácido nucleico heterólogo. Los clones y vectores infectivos son útiles tanto en investigación básica como aplicada, en el desarrollo de sistemas de expresión eficientes de productos de interés (proteínas, enzimas, anticuerpos, etc.), vectores vacunales y terapia génica.

column12: Catalyst for the hydrodesulfurization of residua and heavy crudes
column13: A catalyst for hydrotreating, especially hydrodesulfurization, of residua and heavy crudes is prepared by synthesizing the support from titanium and boehmite, to form either a titanium/alumina support (TiO 2 /Al 2 O 3 ) or a titanium-alumina support (TiO 2 —Al 2 O 3 ) that is thereafter provided with at least one hydrogenating metal from group VIB in oxide form and a promoter from group VIII also in oxide form. The (TiO 2 /Al 2 O 3 ) support is prepared from boehmite, which is peptized by using an inorganic acid, then extruded, calcined and impregnated with a solution containing titanium, while the (TiO 2 —Al 2 O 3 ) support is prepared by admixing boehmite with a titanium-containing solution, peptized using an inorganic acid, extruded and calcined to obtain the titanium-alumina support.

column12: APPARATUS, METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR THE AMBULATORY RECORDING AND ANALYSIS OF INTRACRANIAL PRESSURE AS WELL AS FOR THE AUTOMATIC DETECTION OF ASSOCIATED PATHOLOGIES
column13: Autonomous system for the ambulatory recording of the intracranial pressure of a patient, which system comprises an intracranial pressure sensor which transmits the intracranial pressure signal to a portable apparatus which may control the capture of the signal and may store the latter. The portable apparatus comprises a memory device for storing the intracranial pressure samples, a microcontroller for controlling the intracranial pressure sampling parameters and means for programming said microcontroller. Said parameters are optimized on the basis of experimental results, in accordance with a preset resolution, in order to minimize the power consumption of the system. The system comprises a PC which can be used to process the intracranial pressure samples stored in the memory device of the portable apparatus and can assist with the medical diagnosis of pathologies associated with said recordings.

column12: SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR DIAGNOSING PERMANENT MAGNET SYNCHRONOUS MOTOR AND A RECORDING MEDIUM HAVING COMPUTER READABLE PROGRAM FOR EXECUTING THE METHOD
column13: A system to diagnose a permanent magnet synchronous motor includes a magnetic flux measuring part and a temperature calculating part. The magnetic flux measuring part measures a magnetic flux from a rotor changing depending on a position change of a permanent magnet of the rotor during the operation of the permanent magnet synchronous motor. The temperature calculating part calculates the temperature of the permanent magnet of the rotor by using a preset corresponding relation between temperature and the measured magnetic flux. According to the formation, the present invention is capable of easily measuring the temperature of the permanent magnet of the rotor of the permanent magnet synchronous motor without an external influence and a high-priced extra machine by using the magnetic flux measured by using a linear hall sensor used to identify a position of the permanent magnet of the rotor.

column12: METHOD FOR THE CATALYTIC HYDROPROCESSING OF HEAVY PETROLEUM HYDROCARBONS
column13: The invention relates to a method for the catalytic hydroprocessing of heavy petroleum hydrocarbons with a high concentration of contaminants (metals and asphaltenes), which is performed at low-pressure operating conditions, together with the type of reactor and the type of feedstock. column12: FIXING, CLOSING AND COUPLING DEVICE FOR INTRAVENOUS PERFUSION CATHETERS
column13: The invention relates to a mechanical system for fixing, closing and coupling intravenous perfusion catheters. The system comprises: a thin circular part (2) including at least two holes for subcutaneous fixation (5); one or more central passages (3) for the coupling of lumens; and an externally-threaded hollow cylindrical part (6) projecting from one side, the interior of which is smooth and provided with a locating lug (4). For household use, the system comprises a sealing cap (7) equipped with one or more small-diameter tubes (9) that are coupled in the lumen holes (3), a locating groove (10), a pull element (11), and a threaded blind cap (8) that establishes a hermetic seal with the threaded part (6). For hospital use, the system comprises an intermediate cap (12) equipped with one or more lumen inlets, and a hollow threaded cap (13) allowing same to be hermetically coupled to the threaded part (6).

column12: CARBON SUPPORTED CATALYST FOR DEMETALLATION OF HEAVY CRUDE OIL AND RESIDUE.
column13: A supported carbon having high surface area, high pore volume containing (i) molybdenum (ii) a metal of non noble Group VIII, (iii) phosphorous, is used for hydrometallization of heavy crude oil and residue. The catalyst prepared by chelating agent has higher hydrodesulfurization activity assuming that more dispersed active metals are present on this catalyst. Long run activity studies show that catalyst having only molybdenum supported on activated carbon has good stability with time-on-stream and very high metal retention capacity.

column12: Process for the catalytic hydrotretment of heavy hydrocarbons of petroleum
column13: Two-stage low pressure catalytic hydrotreatment of heavy petroleum hydrocarbons having a high content of contaminants (metals and asphaltenes), is conducted under operating conditions with low-pressure, in a fixed bed or ebullated bed reactor to limit the formation of sediments and sludge in the product and obtain a hydrotreated hydrocarbon of improved properties, with levels of contaminants, API gravity and distillates within the ranges commonly reported in the feedstocks typical to refining schemes. A hydrotreatment catalyst, whose principal effect is the hydrodemetallization and the hydrocracking of asphaltenes of the heavy hydrocarbons of petroleum is used in the first stage, and the second reaction stage employs a hydrotreatment catalyst for a deeper effect of hydrodesulfurization of the heavy petroleum hydrocarbon whose content of total sulfur is reduced to a level required for its treatment in the conventional refining process or for its sale as a hydrocarbon of petroleum with improved properties.

column13: Method of reception (demodulation) of wavelet multicarrier signals-ofmd, corresponding devices to receive. The invention proposes a method of receiving modulated multi-carrier signals in the transmitter with a wavelet-ofdm system based on an elt modulated filter bank. The invention proposes a rapid implementation algorithm that effects the reception of signals, and optionally, a channel equalization stage with a single system coefficient or function per subcarrier. With the modulation schemes used to obtain the system, the proposed invention, comparing it with ofmd, can: a) allow to separate with greater spectral efficiency the information in each of the subcarriers; b) increase the robustness of the system; c) increase the immunity of the system against narrowband interference. column12: USER EQUIPMENT POSITIONING ALGORITHM FOR PERFORMANCE AND CHANNEL STATE INFORMATION TESTS IN MILLIMETER WAVE
column13: In an aspect, a test equipment performs a coarse loop comprising: rotating a position of the UE through a first plurality of equally spaced grid points, determining, at each grid point, whether the grid point passes a first validity check, and, based on the grid point passing the first validity check, recording both the RI and RSRP-B for the grid point, selects a grid point having the highest RSRP-B, and performs a fine loop comprising: rotating the position of the UE through a second plurality of equally spaced grid points, wherein the second plurality of equally spaced grid points are points within a closest vicinity of the grid point having the highest RSRP-B, determining, at each grid point of the second plurality of equally spaced grid points, whether the grid point passes a second validity check, and, based on the grid point passing the second validity check, recording the RSRP-B for the grid point, selects a grid point of the second plurality of equally spaced grid points having the highest RSRP-B, and performs an isolation procedure followed by a REFSENS procedure.

column12: PROCESS FOR THE CATALYTIC HYDROTREATMENT OF HEAVY HYDROCARBONS OF PETROLEUM
column13: The present invention provides a process for the catalytic hydrotreatment of heavy hydrocarbons of petroleum with a high content of contaminants (metals and asphaltenes), which operates in operating conditions with low-pressure, in combination with the type of reactor and the type of feedstock, which together limit the formation of sediments and sludge in the product and obtain a hydrotreated hydrocarbon of improved properties, with levels of contaminants, API gravity and distillates within the ranges commonly reported in the feedstocks typical to refining schemes. More particularly, the present invention comprises the stages of: l) feeding the heavy hydrocarbons of petroleum to a fixed or ebullated-bed reactor packed with a hydrotreatment catalyst, whose principal effect is the hydrodemetallization and the hydrocracking of asphaltenes of the heavy hydrocarbons of petroleum, and, II) feeding the heavy hydrocarbon of petroleum hydrotreated in stage I to a fixed or ebullated-bed reactor with a hydrotreatment catalyst, for a deeper effect of hydrodesulfurization of the heavy hydrocarbon of petroleum, whose content of total sulfur is reduced to a level required for its treatment in the conventional refining process or for its sale as a hydrocarbon of petroleum with improved properties.

column13: "PROCESSO PARA O HIDROTRATAMENTO CATALìTICO DE HIDROCARBONETOS PESADOS DE PETRóLEO". column12: Method of detection of ultrasonic signals with modulation dsss tolerant to the doppler effect (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: The use of direct sequence spread spectrum modulation (dsss) techniques in ultrasonic sensory systems introduces significant improvements over classical systems based on envelope detection. In this type of systems, the detection of signals is done through the use of coupled filters (correlators) that convolute the received signal with the inverted version over time of the emitted patterns. This pattern comparison process is especially sensitive to the movement of the emitter or receiver of ultrasonic signals and their associated doppler effect, given the low propagation speed of these signals compared with that of electromagnetic waves. This invention presents a new method of detecting ultrasonic signals with dsss modulation that allows to carry out the detection of these signals when the transmitter or receiver is in motion, as well as to estimate the speed of this movement. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: METHOD FOR CATALYTIC HYDRO-TREATMENT OF HEAVY HYDROCARBONS OF OIL AND PRODUCT RECEIVED BY THIS METHOD
column13: FIELD: oil and gas industry. ^ SUBSTANCE: here is disclosed group of inventions related to versions of two-stage method of calalytic hydro-treatment of heavy oil hydrocarbons with high content of metals, total sulphur, pyrobitumens and total nitrogen, containing less, than 80% for volume of distillates extracted at 538°C and possessing density API lower, than 32°. According to the first version at the first stage hydrocarbons hydro-metallisation and hydrogen cracking of pyrobitumens are carried out, and at the second stage hydrocarbons hydro-desulphurisation and hydro-denitrogenation are performed; at that both stages of process are performed in a reactor with an immovable layer of catalyst. The second version includes: a) passing hydrogen and hydrocarbon raw material of heavy oil with specific mass (density) less, than 32° API and contents of distillates extracted at 538°C less, than 80% of volume through to the first stage of reaction for hydro-treatment of the said raw materials; at that the said first stage of reaction is performed in the reactor with the immovable layer of catalyst, containing a catalyst of hydro-demetallization and facilitating operation under pressure from 40 to 130 kg/cm2, at temperature from 320° to 450°C, at a volume speed (LHSV) from 0.2 to 3.0 hr-1 and at ratio of hydrogen/hydrocarbon (H2/HC) from 350 to 1.200 In/I with the result of production of hydro-treated heavy hydrocarbons; b) passing hydrogen and the said hydro-treated heavy hydrocarbons through to the second stage of reaction for hydro-treatment in the reactor with the immovable layer of catalyst containing hydro desulphurisation catalyst and facilitating operation under pressure from 40 to 130 kg/cm2, at temperature from 320° to 450°C, at a volume speed (LHSV) from 0.2 to 3.0 hr-1 and at ratio of hydrogen/hydrocarbon (H2/HC) from 350 to 1.200 In/I, at that the amount of sediments formed at each the said first and second stages of reaction is less 0.65% from weight of hydro-treated hydrocarbons. Also one of the inventions of the group refers to the product produced by the method according to the second variant. Employing of the said variant of the method facilitates high degree of metals, sulphur, nitrogen and pyrobitumens extraction and also limits formation of sediments which provides receiving the product after hydro-treatment with improved characteristics. ^ EFFECT: facilitating high degree of metals, sulphur, nitrogen and pyrobitumens extraction and also limits formation of sediments which provides receiving product after hydro-treatment with improved characteristics. ^ 10 cl, 26 tbl, 10 ex, 1 dwg

column12: MONTELUKAST FOR THE TREATMENT OF EROSIVE HAND OSTEOARTHRITIS
column13: The present invention relates to montelukast for use in the treatment of erosive hand osteoarthritis. According to this use, montelukast can be administered either orally or topically, in the form of any suitable pharmaceutical composition. Patients suffering from erosive hand osteoarthritis treated with montelukast showed improvement in clinical symptoms and in radiological parameters, and also reported pain relief and hand functionality improvement.

column12: MONTELUKAST FOR THE TREATMENT OF EROSIVE HAND OSTEOARTHRITIS
column13: The present invention relates to montelukast for use in the treatment of erosive hand osteoarthritis. According to this use, montelukast can be administered either orally or topically, in the form of any suitable pharmaceutical composition. Patients suffering from erosive hand osteoarthritis treated with montelukast showed improvement in clinical symptoms and in radiological parameters, and also reported pain relief and hand functionality improvement.

column12: Montélukast destinée au traitement de l'arthrose de la main
column13: La présente invention concerne du montélukast à utiliser dans le traitement de l'ostéoarthrite érosive de la main. Selon cette utilisation, le montélukast peut être administré soit par voie buccale soit topique, sous la forme d'une quelconque composition pharmaceutique appropriée. Les patients•es souffrant d'ostéoarthrite érosive de la main traités•es avec du montélukast ont présenté une amélioration des symptômes cliniques et des paramètres radiologiques, et ont également rapporté un soulagement de la douleur et une amélioration de la fonctionnalité de la main.

column12: disposição introduzida em pinça ortodontica com garra de suporte para inserção de ligaduras elasticas modulares
column13: “disposição introduzida em pinça ortodôntica com garra de suporte para inserção de ligaduras elásticas modulares”, que se refere a uma nova disposição construtiva aplicada em uma pinça ortodôntica. mais particularmente, a disposição construtiva aplica-se essencialmente no tratamento ortodôntico para a realização de procedimento de inserção de ligaduras elásticas modulares nos braquetes de pacientes em tratamento com aparelhos ortodônticos. sendo assim, os métodos para essas práticas habituais de ortodontistas precisavam ser aperfeiçoadas e a disposição introduzida em pinça ortodôntica com garra de suporte para inserção de ligaduras elástica modulares, solução esta, que para atingir o objetivo, traz uma pinça ortodôntica dispostas de duas hastes paralelamente simétricas, levemente curvadas, a fim de proporcionar uma melhor empunhadura da pinça e melhor posição da mesma para realização da mesma na inserção de ligaduras elásticas modulares, sendo suas extremidades pontiagudas em formato de semi flechas, para proporcionar a inserção no centro da ligadura elástica, que por sua vez, as ligaduras deslizam até as garras de suporte, ou seja, pequenas aberturas ou fresta localizadas logo atrás das semi flechas, no prolongamento das hastes, permitindo ao profissional total controle dos mesmos, podendo ainda envolve-las nos braquetes com maior precisão, facilidade e menor esforço, havendo uma enorme vantagem em ganho de tempo nas consultas, conforto ao paciente beneficiando profissionais e pacientes.

column12: RECOMBINANT VACCINE AGAINST THE PORCINE CIRCOVIRUS, STRENGTHENED WITH AN IMMUNOMODULATOR
column13: The invention relates to a recombinant vaccine against the porcine circovirus type 2, based on a chimeric variant of the protein CAP, which is strengthened with an immunomodulator, preferably porcine interferon alpha. The invention also relates to a synthetic polynucleotide sequence that encodes said protein variant, a recombinant protein of this type, a vector for the expression of genes of interest in the yeast Pichia pastoris which permits the production of the components of the vaccine, an expression cassette, a transformed yeast cell, and a method for the production of a vaccine against porcine circovirus type 2 in yeasts.

column12: Process for partial upgrading of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils for transportation
column13: The present invention relates to a process for the partial upgrading of properties of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oil by low severity catalytic hydrotreatment in only one reaction step. The process of the present invention is obtained upgraded oil with properties required for its transportation from offshore platforms either to maritime terminal or to refining centers. The process reduces the viscosity of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oil, and decreases the concentration of impurities, such as sulfur, nitrogen, and metals, in such a way that heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils can be transported to maritime terminals or to refining centers. The process increases the lifetime of the catalyst and decreased operating costs by reducing consumption of utilities because the operation of the process is carried out at lower severity. The partially upgraded oils obtained in this process can be transported directly to the maritime terminals or to existing refineries.

column12: PROCESS FOR PARTIAL UPGRADING OF HEAVY AND/OR EXTRA-HEAVY CRUDE OILS FOR TRANSPORTATION.
column13: The present invention relates to a process for the partial upgrading of properties of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oil, mainly for being transported, by low severity catalytic hydrotreatment in only one reaction step, under low severity operation conditions (temperatures and pressures lower than 400°C and 51 Kg/cm2). The process of the present invention is intended to obtain upgraded oil with properties required for its transportation from offshore platforms either to maritime terminal or to refining centers. The main technical contributions of the process of the present invention, compared with conventional refining processes, are the following: The process reduces the viscosity of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oil, and decreases the concentration of impurities, such as: sulfur, nitrogen, and metals, in such a way that heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils can be transported to maritime terminals or to refining centers. The process increases the lifetime of the catalyst and decreas ed operating costs by reducing consumption of utilities because the operation of the process is carried out at lower severity. The partially upgraded oils obtained in this process can be transported directly to the maritime terminals or to existing refineries.

column12: EMULSION CONCENTRATES CONTAINING AN OXADIAZOLE AND A CHLOROACETAMIDE
column13: The invention relates to emulsion concentrates that contain the following components: A) at least one agrochemical active substance from the oxadiazole group, B) at least one agrochemical active substance from the chloroacetamide group, C) at least one solvent from the N-alkyl pyrrolidone group, D) at least one solvent from the dimethyl fatty acid amide group, E) at least one solvent from the group of aliphatic or aromatic hydrocarbons, F) at least one ionic surfactant, and G) at least one non-ionic surfactant. Along with high active substance stability in the formulations, an improved biological effect is achieved with the same amounts being used.

column12: VACUNA RECOMBINANTE CONTRA EL CIRCOVIRUS PORCINO POTENCIADA CON UN INMUNOMODULADOR
column13: La presente invención provee una vacuna recombinante contra el circovirus porcino de tipo 2 basada en una variante quimérica de la proteína Cap, la cual es potenciada con un inmunomodulador, preferentemente interferón alfa porcino. Adicionalmente, la invención divulga una secuencia polinucleotídica sintética que codifica dicha variante proteica, una proteína recombinante como tal, un vector para la expresión de genes de interés en la levadura Pichia pastoris que permite obtener los componentes de la vacuna, un casete de expresión, una célula de levadura transformada y un método para la producción de una vacuna contra circovirus porcino de tipo 2 en levaduras.

column12: DEVICE FOR EARLY DETECTION OF DAMAGE IN ONE GEOMEMBRANE AND PROCEDURE FOR SUCH DETECTION (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Device that allows detecting damages in a geomembrane early, and procedure to carry out said detection. The geomembrane includes configurations that follow a pattern, the device comprises data storage means, a data processor, lighting means for illuminating the configurations and a camera for recording light reflection in said configurations of the geomembrane. The method for the early detection of damages in a geomembrane and with a device such as those described comprises the following steps: a. introduction into the data storage means of the pattern of the configurations; b. illumination of the configurations with the lighting means; c. record of the reflection of the light in said configurations with the camera; d. checking if the reflection of the light in the configurations follows the stored pattern; e. establishment of damage.

column12: Photoprotector and/or photoimmunoprotector compositions of the skin and their uses
column13: The composition comprises of a component A selected from a hydroxylated derivative of benzoic acid or of cinamic acid, their esters, amides or salts, a glycoside of a hexose, and their mixtures; and a component B selected from quinic acid, shikimic acid, their alkaline metal or alkaline earth salts, their methyl esters, and mixtures of the same. This composition is suitable for protecting the skin against ultraviolet radiation coming from the sun or artificial sources, such as those used in phototherapy units and in sun tanning rooms. For application in the field of dermatology and nutrition, and, in particular, in the photoprotection of the skin and mucosa, photo-ageing and photocarcinogenesis, including protection of the immune system associated with the skin.

column12: PROCESSO DE EXTRAÇÃO DE LÍTIO DE MINÉRIOS E CONCENTRADOS POR ATIVAÇÃO MECÂNICA E REAÇÃO COM ÁCIDO SULFÚRICO
column13: A PRESENTE INVENÇÃO REFERE-SE A UM PROCESSO DE EXTRAÇÃO DE LÍTIO DE MINÉRIOS OU CONCENTRADOS DE MINERAIS DE LÍTIO, ATRAVÉS DA COMBINAÇÃO DE TRÊS OPERAÇÕES UNITÁRIAS, A ATIVAÇÃO MECÂNICA DO MINÉRIO OU DO CONCENTRADO, SEGUIDA DE REAÇÃO POR DIGESTÃO COM ÁCIDO SULFÚRICO CONCENTRADO E LIXIVIAÇÃO COM ÁGUA. A ATIVAÇÃO MECÂNICA PROCESSA-SE ATRAVÉS DE MOAGEM DE ALTA ENERGIA, QUE PROMOVE A ALTERAÇÃO DA ESTRUTURA DO MINERAL, TORNANDO-O AMORFO E MAIS REATIVO, O QUE PERMITE QUE A ETAPA SUBSEQUENTE DE REAÇÃO POR DIGESTÃO ÁCIDA PARA A FORMAÇÃO DO SULFATO DE LÍTIO, A TEMPERATURA INFERIOR A 200ºC, SEJA EFICIENTE E RÁPIDA. COMO RESULTADO DAS ETAPAS ANTERIORES, O SÓLIDO REAGIDO CONTÉM SULFATO DE LÍTIO QUE É DISSOLVIDO NA ETAPA SUBSEQUENTE DE LIXIVIAÇÃO COM ÁGUA. A RECUPERAÇÃO DO LÍTIO CONTIDO NAS FASES MINERAIS É SUPERIOR A 80%, PODENDO EM CONDIÇÕES OTIMIZADAS ATINGIR MAIS DE 90%.

column12: Induction coil carrier device for use in induction cook field, has plastic body with retaining units for retaining induction coil arrangement, where body has two areas, which are designed from plastics with different temperature resistances
column13: The device has a plastic body (10) with retaining units (12a-12h) for retaining an induction coil arrangement within a cooking surface of an induction cook field. The plastic body consists of two areas (16a, 16b), which are designed from plastics having different temperature resistances. The retaining units are attached to the area (16a) having higher temperature resistances. The retaining units are designed as supports, which lunge out from the plastic body. An independent claim is also included for a method for producing a plastic body.

column12: PROCESS OF LITHIUM EXTRACTION FROM ORES AND CONCENTRATES BY MECHANICAL ACTIVATION AND REACTION WITH SULPHURIC ACID
column13: The present invention refers to a process of extraction of lithium from ores or lithium mineral concentrates, through the combination of three unitary operations, the mechanical activation of the ore or of the concentrate, followed by the reaction by digestion with concentrate sulphuric acid and leaching with water. The mechanical activation is processed through the high energy milling, which promotes the alteration of the mineral structure, making it amorphous and more reactive, which allows that the subsequent step of the reaction by acid digestion to the formation of lithium sulphate, at temperature bellow 200°C, to be efficient and fast. As a result of the previous steps, the reacted solid contains lithium sulphate that is dissolved in the subsequent step of leaching with water. The recovery of the lithium contained in the mineral phases is higher than 80%, and in optimized conditions it can achieve more than 90%.

column12: LEAK-TIGHT TRAY FOR TRANSPORTING WET PRODUCTS
column13: The present invention relates to a leak-tight tray for transporting wet products formed from a compact cardboard sheet (1) with main folding lines defining a base (3) and four side walls (4, 5) facing one another in twos. The tray comprises a tab (2) arranged in each of the four corners of the base, where each of the tabs in turn comprises two folding lines (21) joining it to two side walls and a third diagonal folding line (23) running from the corner of the base to a free edge (22) of the tab, where said tab is folded towards the inside of the tray when the side walls are raised during assembly of the tray.

column12: PROCESS OF HYDROCONVERSION-DISTILLATION OF HEAVY AND/OR EXTRA-HEAVY CRUDE OILS.
column13: The present invention relates to a process of the refining industry of petroleum: hydroconversion-distillation of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils, which comprises four stages:. 1) desalting and separation of the feedstock; 2) catalytic hydrotreating of light fraction (optional); 3) catalytic hydroconversion of heavy fraction, and 4) distillation of hydrotreated products. In this regard, it is important to point out that, by means of the process of the present invention products that can be processed in conventional refining schemes, designed to operate with light and intermediate crude oils are obtained.. Among the main technical contributions of the process of the present invention, compared with conventional refining processes are the following: increases the yield of distillate fractions and decreases the concentration of pollutants such as: sulfur, nitrogen, metals, etc., favoring the downstream plants operating at less severe conditions with the consequent increase in the lif etime of the catalysts and the reduced operating costs by reducing the consumption of utilities. Allows existing and conventional refineries to process larger amounts of heavy and extra-heavy crude oils. The light and heavy fractions obtained can be fed to the atmospheric distillation column in existing refineries, because their properties are similar to those of light and intermediates crude oils which are usually processed.

column12: MULTIFUNCTIONAL GENETIC CONSTRUCTIONS HAVING A HIGH CAPACITY TO INHIBIT THE EXPRESSION OF CCR5 ON THE CELL SURFACE
column13: The invention relates to multifunctional genetic constructions which can mimic the HIV-1-resistant phenotype in individuals with mutations that functionally inactivate the CCR5 chemokine receptor. In this way, the invention relates to various therapeutic genetic constructions which can inhibit specifically the expression of the aforementioned receptor in human cells and to retroviral vectors which can be used to introduce therapeutic genes into said cells. Moreover, the invention relates to a genetic transduction system based on the above-mentioned vectors with applications in experimental animal models and clinical treatments for HIV-1. The functional inactivation systems outlined herein can also be used to research and treat other human pathologies involving the CCR5 protein or other chemokine receptors.

column12: Procedure and system for the detection of electrical consumption patterns in a home indicative of health problems (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: The invention describes a procedure for detecting electrical consumption patterns in a home indicative of health problems of a person who lives in said home, comprising: obtaining a signal representative of electrical consumption in the home; analyze the signal to extract characteristic parameters representative of the electrical consumption corresponding to individual household appliances; analyze the characteristic parameters to identify which part of the electrical consumption of the house corresponds to each of said individual electrical appliances and determine the moments of activation and deactivation of each one of said electrical appliances; and analyze the moments of activation and deactivation of electrical appliances to identify anomalous situations compatible with a fainting of the person who lives in the house. The invention also describes a system designed to carry out said procedure. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: Bandeja estanca para transporte de productos húmedos
column13: Bandeja estanca para el transporte de productos húmedos formada a partir de una plancha de cartón compacto (1) con unas líneas de plegado principales que definen una base (3) y cuatro paredes laterales (4, 5) enfrentadas dos a dos, en la que una pestaña (2) está dispuesta en cada una de las cuatro esquinas de la base, en la que cada una de las pestañas comprende a su vez dos líneas de plegado (21) que la unen a dos paredes laterales y una tercera línea de plegado diagonal (23) que discurre desde la esquina de la base hasta un borde libre (22) de la pestaña, en la que dicha pestaña se pliega hacia el interior de la bandeja cuando se elevan las paredes laterales durante el ensamblado de la bandeja, caracterizada porque al menos una de las paredes laterales además comprende en sus extremos unas prolongaciones (41) definidas por unas líneas de plegado (42) que coinciden con los bordes verticales de la bandeja, en la que las prolongaciones comprenden dos líneas de plegado adicionales (43, 44) que dividen cada una de las prolongaciones en 3 porciones y forman una estructura poliédrica que tiene una sección triangular cuando la porción intermedia se pliega hacia el interior de la bandeja y la porción más exterior se pliega hacia el exterior de la bandeja quedando colocada contra la pared lateral.

column12: PHOTOPROTECTIVE AND/OR PHOTOIMMUNOPROTECTIVE COMPOSITIONS FOR THE SKIN AND USES THEREOF
column13: The composition comprises of a component A selected from a hydroxylated derivative of benzoic acid or of cinamic acid, their esters, amides or salts, a glycoside of a hexose, and their mixtures; and a component B selected from quinic acid, shikimic acid, their alkaline metal or alkaline earth salts, their methyl esters, and mixtures of the same. This composition is suitable for protecting the skin against ultraviolet radiation coming from the sun or artificial sources, such as those used in phototherapy units and in sun tanning rooms. For application in the field of dermatology and nutrition, and, in particular, in the photoprotection of the skin and mucosa, photo-ageing and photocarcinogenesis, including protection of the immune system associated with the skin.

column12: Kochfeld mit einem bewegbaren Heizelement
column13: Kochfeld mit einer Kochfläche (10) mit mehreren Heizzonen (12a–12o) zum Aufstellen von Kochgeschirr (22), mit zumindest einem unter der Kochfläche (10) angeordneten, bewegbaren Heizelement (14a–14d) und mit einem Aktuator (16a–16d) zum Bewegen des wenigstens einen bewegbaren Heizelements (14a–14d), gekennzeichnet durch eine Steuereinheit (20), die zum Betätigen des Aktuators (16a–16d) abhängig von wenigstens einer erkannten Größe und Position eines auf die Kochfläche (10) aufgestellten Kochgeschirrs (22) ausgelegt ist, wobei die Steuereinheit (20) dazu vorgesehen ist, abhängig von der erkannten Größe des Kochgeschirrs (22) eine Heizzone (12a–12o) zum Heizen des Kochgeschirrs (22) zu definieren und in zumindest einem Betriebszustand, in welchem zwei unterschiedliche Kochgeschirrteile (22a, 22b) auf der Kochfläche (10) detektiert wurden, das zumindest eine bewegbare Heizelement (14a–14d) abwechselnd in zumindest zwei räumlich getrennte Heizzonen (12a–12o) zum Beheizen von zwei unterschiedlichen Kochgeschirrteilen (22a, 22b) zu verfahren.

column12: Process of hydroconversion-distillation of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils
column13: A process for hydroconversion-distillation of heavy and/or extra-heavy crude oils, which comprises four stages: 1) desalting and separation of the feedstock;2) catalytic hydrotreating of light fraction (optional);3) catalytic hydroconversion of heavy fraction, and4) distillation of hydrotreated products to provide products that can be processed in conventional refining schemes designed to operate with light and intermediate crude oils.

column12: HOB WITH A MOVABLE HEATING ELEMENT
column13: The invention is based on a hob with a cooking area (10) with a plurality of heating zones (12a - 12o) on which cooking utensils (22) are positioned, with at least one movable heating element (14a - 14d), which is arranged below the cooking area (10), and with an actuator (16a - 16d) for moving the at least one movable heating element (14a - 14d). column12: Kochfeld mit einem bewegbaren Heizelement
column13: Die Erfindung geht aus von einem Kochfeld mit einer Kochfläche (10) mit mehreren Heizzonen (12a–12o) zum Aufstellen von Kochgeschirr (22), mit zumindest einem unter der Kochfläche (10) angeordneten, bewegbaren Heizelement (14a–14d) und mit einem Aktuator (16a–16d) zum Bewegen des wenigstens einen bewegbaren Heizelements (14a–14d), und mit einer Steuereinheit (20), die zum Betätigen des Aktuators (16a–16d) abhängig von wenigstens einer Betriebskenngröße (D) ausgelegt ist. Um gattungsgemäße Kochfelder flexibler zu gestalten, wird vorgeschlagen, dass die Steuereinheit (20) dazu vorgesehen ist, in zumindest einem Betriebszustand das bewegbare Heizelement (14a–14d) abwechselnd in zumindest zwei räumlich getrennte Heizzonen (12a–12o) zum Beheizen von zwei Kochgeschirrteilen (22a, 22b) zu verfahren.

column12: Kochfeld mit einem bewegbaren Heizelement
column13: Kochfeld mit einer Kochfläche (10) mit mehreren Heizzonen (12a–12o) zum Aufstellen von Kochgeschirr (22), mit zumindest einem unter der Kochfläche (10) angeordneten, bewegbaren Heizelement (14a–14d) und mit einem Aktuator (16a–16d) zum Bewegen des wenigstens einen bewegbaren Heizelements (14a–14d), und mit einer Steuereinheit (20), die zum Betätigen des Aktuators (16a–16d) abhängig von wenigstens einer Betriebskenngröße (D) ausgelegt ist und mit einer Sensoranordnung (18) zum Erkennen einer Position und/oder Größe von auf der Kochfläche (10) aufgestelltem Kochgeschirr (22), wobei das zumindest eine bewegbare Heizelement (14a–14d) als induktives Heizelement ausgebildet ist, und wobei die Sensoranordnung (18) zum automatischen Erkennen einer Position und/oder Größe von auf der Kochfläche (10) aufgestelltem Kochgeschirr zumindest eine Kenngröße einer Impedanz des bewegbaren induktiven Heizelements (14a–14d) in zumindest zwei Positionen vergleicht, dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass die Steuereinheit (20) dazu vorgesehen ist, abhängig von der erkannten Größe des Kochgeschirrs (22) eine Heizzone (12a–12o) zum Heizen des Kochgeschirrs (22) zu definieren und dass die Steuereinheit dazu vorgesehen ist, in einer Heizphase wenigstens eines der einer Heizzone (12a–12o) zugeordneten bewegbaren Heizelemente (14a–14d) so zu bewegen, dass eine der Kochfläche (10) zugewandte Fläche des Heizelements (14a–14d) die Heizzone (12a–12o) überstreicht derart, dass eine mittlere Heizleistung über eine Fläche der Heizzone homogenisiert wird.

column12: disposição introduzida em pinça ortodôntica para bráquetes com espelho removível
column13: que se refere a uma nova disposição construtiva aplicada em uma pinça ortodôntica para bráquete. mais particularmente, a disposição construtiva aplica-se essencialmente no tratamento ortodôntico para a realização de procedimento de inserção de bráquetes nos dentes de pacientes em tratamento com aparelhos fixos. sendo assim, os métodos para essas práticas habituais de ortodontistas precisavam ser aperfeiçoadas, pois o procedimento é demorado devido a quantidade de vezes que o profissional precisa deixar a boca do paciente para buscar outro instrumento auxiliar como o espelho para visualizar as inserções de bráquetes que foram feitos, e a disposição introduzida em pinça ortodôntica para bráquete com espelho removível, solução esta, que para atingir o objetivo, traz um espelho com uma rosca tipo ?macho? acoplada no meio da estrutura na parte posterior do espelho, cujo encaixe se dá através do rosqueamento da mesma no orifício de rosca tipo ?fêmea? introduzido sobre a junção das hastes na estrutura da pinça ortodôntica para bráquete, para que o profissional tenha em mãos uma única ferramenta para executar essa prática, possibilitando ao profissional total controle da situação, permitindo inserções com maior precisão, facilidade e menor esforço, havendo uma enorme vantagem em ganho de tempo nas consultas, conforto ao paciente beneficiando profissionais e pacientes.

column12: COMPOSICIÓN FUNGICIDA CONCENTRADA DE AZOXISTROBINA, CIPROCONAZOL Y CLOROTALONILO DE ALTA CARGA, FORMULACIONES Y MÉTODO PARA CONTROLAR ROYA-ASIÁTICA Y OTRAS ENFERMEDADES
column13: La presente invención describe una composición fungicida concentrada de azoxistrobina, ciproconazol y clorotalonilo de alta carga y de otras formulaciones que contienen clorotalonilo con efecto fotoprotector de la azoxistrobina, ciproconazol y de otros ingredientes activos y/o derivadas de esta composición, así como el método de tratamiento de enfermedades provocadas por hongos. Reivindicación 1: Composición fungicida caracterizada por contener: como ingredientes activos, Clorotalonilo en una concentración de 46,99% a 50,75% m/m de la composición, con efecto fotoprotector de los demás ingredientes activos, Azoxistrobina en una concentración de 3,58% a 4,38% m/m de la composición y Ciproconazol en una concentración de 1,02% a 1,38% m/m de la composición; Propilenglicol en una concentración de 1,00% a 20,00% m/m de la composición; 1,2-bencisotiazolin-3-ona en una concentración de 0,10% a 1,00% m/m de la composición; Poli(dimetilsiloxano) en una concentración de 0,50% a 2,00% m/m de la composición; Goma xantana en una concentración de 0,05% a 0,20% m/m de la composición; y Agua en una concentración de 20,00% a 40,00% m/m de la composición. Reivindicación 7: Formulación fungicida, de acuerdo con la composición definida en las reivindicaciones 1 y 2, caracterizada por estar compuesta de: Azoxistrobina en una concentración de 3,58% a 4,38% m/m de la composición; Ciproconazol en una concentración de 1,02% a 1,38% m/m de la composición; Clorotalonilo en una concentración de 46,99% a 50,75% m/m de la composición; Propilenglicol en una concentración de 3,00% a 10,00% m/m de la composición; Polietilen-polipropilenglicol éter monobutílico en una concentración de 5,00% a 10,00% m/m de la composición; Poli(dimetilsiloxano) en una concentración de 0,50% a 2,00% m/m de la composición; 1,2-bencisotiazolin-3-ona en una concentración de 0,10% a 1,00% m/m de la composición; Goma xantana en una concentración de 0,05% a 0,20% m/m de la composición; Condensado de alquilnaftalensulfonato de sodio y formaldehído en una concentración de 1,00% a 5,00% m/m de la composición; y Agua en una concentración de 20,00% a 40,00% m/m de la composición.

column12: SYSTEM, METHOD AND DEVICE FOR MANAGING PUBLIC UTILITY FLUIDS
column13: The invention generally relates to systems, methods and devices that are used to: take measurements, quality indicators and prevention indicators from the device; offer usage prepayment options; suspend and reconnect public utilities, such as water, electrical power, residential gas or any other public utility; and, in addition, control commercial and/or distribution losses instantly and automatically in residential public utility companies. The invention also relates to the real-time transmission and reception of data between the user and the relevant public utility company. More specifically, the invention relates to an integral fluid control and measurement system.

column12: processo obtenção de urânio de alta pureza a partir do licor de ácido fosfórico
column13: resumo resumo da patente de invenção "processo obtenção de urânio de alta pureza a partir do licor de ácido fosfórico". a presente invenção refere-se a um processo de extração por solvente, em baterias de misturadores-decantadores de múltiplos estágios, com uma mistura de três extratantes para obtenção de urânio de alta pureza contido em compostos ou minérios que contenham urânio e fosfatos associados. o processo compreende as seguintes etapas: licor de ácido fosfórico proveniente da lixiviação ácida com ácido sulfurico de rochas fosfáticas com urânio associado em qualquer concentração; remoção de matéria orgânica do licor de alimentação por extração por solvente com uma nova mistura de extratantes; oxidação do u-lv a u-vi com água oxigenada; extração do urânio também com uma nova mistura de extratantes de alta eficiência, objeto desta invenção, com uma razão de fases aquosa /orgânica maior que 7 e com uma concentração de urânio no licor de alimentação maior que 1,5 g/1; remoção de impurezas como o fe e mo e outros contaminantes com ácido oxálico; remoção de terras raras com ácido sulfúrico; neutralização da fase orgânica com água; e finalmente a reextração do urânio da fase orgânica carregada com uma mistura de bicarbonato e carbonato de sódio formando o tri- carbonato de urânio e sódio doravante chamado de tcus. a última etapa do processo se refere à regeneração do solvente para a remoção do ion sódio extraído na etapa de reextração do urânio que é realizado pela fase aquosa de ácido súlfurico proveniente da etapa da reextração das terras raras. o tcus obtido de alta pureza pode ser convertido ao dus (na2u201), u0~.2h20 (peróxido de uranila) ou ao dua (nh 2 u20 7) por metodologias já conhecidas.

column12: Cooking hob with a metallicly covered cover plate. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Cooking hob with a metal-coated cover plate and method for making a metal-coated cover plate. The invention is based on a cooking hob with at least one inductor (10) and a cover plate (12) of glass or glass-ceramic, which has on one side a coating with a metal layer (14). To improve an electromagnetic compatibility of a cooking hob with a coating consisting of a metal plate, it is proposed that a coating area (16), covering the inductor (10), of the metal layer (14) be electrically isolated from an environment area (18) of the layer (14), which surrounds the coating area (16). A method is also proposed for isolating the metallic coating covering the inductor with respect to the metallic coating of an area of its environment, which consists in incorporating in the metallic layer (14) a discontinuity (20) that delimits the coating area (16). ). (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column12: Crossbeam for metric gauge ballast track and railway (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)
column13: Crossbeam for ballast track with metric gauge and railway track. The present invention has its application within the industrial sector dedicated to the manufacture of railway tracks and sleepers used in these tracks and, more specifically, the invention relates to a sleeper with application on railway tracks, and specifically, in railroad tracks of metric gauge. The invention provides a sleeper capable of stabilizing the track in all three directions and, in a special way, in the transverse direction, the least studied of the three. Through a screed, the sleeper is able to develop the necessary effort to cope with the instabilities originated in the transverse direction by the actions to which the road is exposed. In a first plane, the invention provides solutions to the transversal dynamics of the track, in a second plane, to the longitudinal dynamics and in a third plane, to the vertical dynamics of the track, to the latter in a less predominant way since it will use elements known in the art. (Machine-translation by Google Translate, not legally binding)

column13: Die Erfindung geht aus von einer Kochfeldvorrichtung (12), insbesondere einer Induktionskochfeldvorrichtrung, mit zumindest einer Glaseinheit (14) und zumindest einer als Vielschichtstruktur ausgebildeten Beschichtung (16), die auf zumindest einem Teilbereich zumindest einer Hauptfläche der Glaseinheit (14) angeordnet ist und die zumindest zwei Schichten (20, 21, 22, 23, 24) aufweist. column12: Domestic appliance
column13: The apparatus (12) has a coating (16) configured as a multilayer structure and coated on a subregion of a main face of a glass unit (14), where the coating comprises two layers, one of the layers is formed by semiconducting material and the other layer is formed by semiconducting material or insulating material. The glass unit is designed as a cooktop plate unit. The coating is configured to produce metallic appearance. An electronic unit (60) measures and evaluates electrical characteristics of the former layer formed by semiconducting material, and detects a safety parameter. The subregion is formed as cohesive face and a closed line. The main face is formed as a continuous kink-free face.

column12: EQUIPMENT FOR THE AUTOMATIC ASSESSMENT OF ROAD SIGNS AND PANELS
column13: The invention relates to a device for automatic data acquisition from traffic signs and panels, said device performing, for said purpose, a retroreflection measurement of the white element of said signs or panels, and a measurement of the contrast between the white element of the sign or panel and a characteristic element of same (borders or text) in order to ensure a particular level of legibility. To this end, a vehicle (1) is equipped with a pulsed infrared illumination system (3), a system of stereoscopic cameras (2), a GPS (11), an odometer (12), a computer (5) mounted on an industrial rack, a data storage system (8), an event keyboard (7), and a TFT monitor (6) for viewing results. The infrared illumination system (3) is synchronised with the cameras (2). In this way, the infrared illuminator (3) illuminates the road area in alternate images, thereby providing illuminated road images and non-illuminated road images.

column12: SYNTHESIS PROCESS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF QUARTERNARY CATIONIC SALTS THAT ARE USEFUL AS CHEMICAL TRACERS IN CARBONATE RESERVOIRS, AND PRODUCTS PRODUCED WITH SAME.
column13: The invention relates to a process for the production of organofluoride quarternary cationic salts, comprising the following steps: a) adding a base; b) suspending the base in a suitable polar organic solvent; c) including an alkylating agent via slow addition; d) slowly adding an organofluoride substrate; e) heating the reaction mixture produced in the preceding step d); f) bringing the reaction mixture to ambient temperature; g) filtering the reaction mixture under vacuum, washing the remaining solid with a polar organic solvent; h) accelerating the evaporation of the solvent to complete dryness, producing a whitish solid; i) washing the solid with a non-polar organic solvent; j) purifying the compound produced in the preceding step i), using a polar or non-polar organic solvent, wherein the cationic salts produced with this method are used as chemical tracers to determine the heterogeneity in carbonate-type oil fields.

column12: COMBINATION OF IBUPROFEN AND TRAMADOL FOR RELIEVING PAIN
column13: The present invention relates to the combination of ibuprofen in the form of a pharmaceutically acceptable salt, and tramadol, or a pharmaceutical acceptable salt thereof, for use in the treatment of pain in humans, wherein the dosage of ibuprofen in the combination is comprised between 350 mg and 450 mg and the dosage of tramadol is comprised between 35 mg and 40 mg, expressed as equivalent weight of tramadol hydrochloride. The combination is suitable for the treatment of moderate to severe pain, of chronic or acute origin, and is particularly effective for those patients suffering from more intense pain. It also relates to a pharmaceutical composition comprising said fixed-dose combination of ibuprofen and tramadol.

column12: Combinación de ibuprofeno y tramadol para aliviar el dolor
column13: La presente invención se refiere a la combinación de ibuprofeno en forma de una sal farmacéuticamente aceptable, y tramadol, o una sal farmacéuticamente aceptable del mismo, para uso en el tratamiento del dolor en humanos, en donde la dosis de ibuprofeno en la combinación está comprendida entre 350 mg y 450 mg y la dosis de tramadol está comprendida entre 35 mg y 40 mg, expresada como peso equivalente de clorhidrato de tramadol. column12: USE OF CK2 INHIBITOR FOR THE TREATMENT AND CHEMOSENSIBILIZATION OF REFRACTORY TUMORS TO ANTICANCER DRUGS.
column13: The present invention relates to a pharmaceutical combination that includes a casein kinase 2 phosphorylation inhibitor (called p15) and cytostatics used in cancer chemotherapy, which are administered simultaneously, separately or sequentially. The preferred cytostatics are platinums, taxans, vinca alkaloids, 5-fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, etoposide, mitomycin C, imatinib, iressa and velcade (bortezomib). Synergy between peptide p15 and the anticancer chemical compounds means that the effective concentration of each cytostatic in the combination is between 1 and 2 orders of magnitude less than that corresponding to cytostatics alone. Consequently, the combination described in the invention has a much lower toxicity than that reported for anticancer cytostatics, which represents a crucial advantage in their use in cancer treatment. Additionally, administered sequentially, the combination gives rise to the chemosensitization of refractory tumours to the cytostatics mentioned by means of pre-treatment with peptide p15.

column12: Combinação de ibuprofeno e tramadol para alívio da dor
column13: combinação de ibuprofeno e tramadol para alívio da dor. a presente invenção refere-se à combinação de ibuprofeno na forma de um sal farmaceuticamente aceitável e tramadol, ou um sal farmacêutico aceitável do mesmo, para uso no tratamento da dor em seres humanos, em que a dosagem de ibuprofeno na combinação está compreendida entre 350 mg e 450 mg e a dosagem de tramadol está compreendida entre 35 mg e 40 mg, expressas como peso equivalente de cloridrato de tramadol. a combinação é adequada para o tratamento da dor moderada a grave, de origem crônica ou aguda, e é particularmente eficaz para os pacientes que sofrem de dor mais intensa. refere-se também a uma composição farmacêutica compreendendo a referida combinação de dose fixa de ibuprofeno e tramadol.

column12: A CURVED COMPOSITE PART AND METHOD FOR MANUFACTURING THEREOF
column13: The invention refers to a curved composite part (1) for an aircraft, comprising a composite stack of layers (6), each of the layers (6', 6", 6"', 6"") including reinforcing fibers (7) substantially aligned with at least one direction of a unique Cartesian coordinate reference system (2). Preferably, the layers (6', 6", 6"', 6"") that include fibers (7) whose orientation is secant to the bending line of the inner flange (5) of the part (1) are disposed in overlapping layer segments (8). Preferably, each one of these overlapping layer segments (8) is aligned with the same at least direction of the Cartesian coordinate reference system (2) with which the rest of the fibers (7) of the previous layer have been substantially aligned.

column12: Combination of ibuprofen and tramadol for relieving pain
column13: Prezenta invenţie se referă la combinaţia de ibuprofen sub formă de sare acceptabilă farmaceutic şi tramadol sau o sare acceptabilă farmaceutic a acestuia, pentru utilizare în tratamentul durerii la oameni, în care doza de ibuprofen în combinaţie este cuprinsă între 350 mg şi 450 mg şi doza de tramadol este cuprinsă între 35 mg şi 40 mg, exprimată ca greutate echivalentă a clorhidratului de tramadol. Combinaţia este potrivită pentru tratamentul durerii moderate până la severe, de origine cronică sau acută şi este deosebit de eficientă pentru acei pacienţi care suferă de dureri mai intense. De asemenea, se referă la o compoziţie farmaceutică care cuprinde respectiva combinaţie în doză fixă de ibuprofen şi tramadol.

column12: Combinaison d'ibuprofène et de tramadol pour soulager la douleur
column13: La présente invention concerne la combinaison d'ibuprofène sous la forme d'un sel pharmaceutiquement acceptable, et de tramadol, ou d'un sel pharmaceutiquement acceptable de celui-ci, destinée à être utilisée dans le traitement de la douleur chez l'être humain, le dosage d'ibuprofène dans la combinaison étant compris entre 350 mg et 450 mg et le dosage du tramadol étant compris entre 35 mg et 40 mg, exprimés en poids équivalent de chlorhydrate de tramadol. La combinaison est appropriée pour le traitement de douleurs modérées à sévères, d'origine chronique ou aiguë, et est particulièrement efficace pour les patients souffrant de douleurs plus intenses. L'invention concerne également une composition pharmaceutique comprenant ladite combinaison à dose fixe d'ibuprofène et de tramadol.

column12: USE OF CK2 INHIBITOR FOR THE TREATMENT AND CHEMOSENSIBILIZATION OF REFRACTORY TUMORS TO ANTICANCER DRUGS
column13: The present invention relates to a pharmaceutical combination that includes a casein kinase 2 phosphorylation inhibitor (called p15) and cytostatics used in cancer chemotherapy, which are administered simultaneously, separately or sequentially. The preferred cytostatics are platinums, taxans, vinca alkaloids, 5-fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, etoposide, mitomycin C, imatinib, iressa and velcade (bortezomib). Synergy between peptide p15 and the anticancer chemical compounds means that the effective concentration of each cytostatic in the combination is between 1 and 2 orders of magnitude less than that corresponding to cytostatics alone. Consequently, the combination described in the invention has a much lower toxicity than that reported for anticancer cytostatics, which represents a crucial advantage in their use in cancer treatment. Additionally, administered sequentially, the combination gives rise to the chemosensitization of refractory tumours to the cytostatics mentioned by means of pre-treatment with peptide p15.

column12: USE OF CK2 INHIBITOR FOR THE TREATMENT AND CHEMOSENSIBILIZATION OF REFRACTORY TUMORS TO ANTICANCER DRUGS
column13: This invention is related to a pharmaceutical combination that contains a Casein kinase 2 (CK2) peptide inhibitor (termed P15) along with the standard chemotherapeutic drugs used in cancer treatment and which are administered together, separated or sequentially. The chemothearapeutic drugs include cisplatin, taxol, alkaloids from Vinca, 5-fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, etoposide, mitomicin C, imatinib, iressa and velcade (vortezomib). The synergism between the P15 peptide and the anticancer drugs achieves an efficient concentration of each cytostatic drug in the combination which is from 10- to 100-fold lower than that for each cytostatic drug alone. The pharmaceutical combination described in this invention exhibits lower toxicity compared to that reported by the anticancer therapeutics and therefore, it represents a crucial advantage for its use in cancer therapy. Furthermore, the sequential administration of this pharmaceutical combination through the pretreatment with the P15 peptide leads to the chemo sensibilization of refractory tumors to the anticancer therapeutics.

column12: COMBINACION FARMACÉUTICA PARA EL TRATAMIENTO Y/O QUIMIOSENSIBILIZACION DE TUMORES REFRACTARIOS A DROGAS ANTICANCERIGENAS
column13: Combinacion farmacéutica que incluye un inhibidor de la fosforilacion de la caseína Kinasa 2 (denominado P15) y los citostáticos usados en la quimioterapia del cáncer los cuales son administrados simultáneos, separados o secuencialmente. La sinergia entre el péptido P15 y los compuestos químicos anticancerígenos, hace que la combinacion descrita tenga una toxicidad mucho menor que para los citostáticos anticancerígenos lo cual representa una ventaja crucial para su uso en el tratamiento del cáncer. Adicionalmente, la combinacion administrada de manera secuencial produce la quimiosensibilizacion de tumores refractarios a los citostáticos mencionados mediante el pretratamiento con el péptido P15.

column12: Drug delivery system based on biologically active compound functionalized calcium phosphate nanoparticles from Euphorbia pekinensis extract and uses thereof
column13: The present invention relates to a composition comprising biologically active molecules esculetin and euphorbidin, which have antineoplastic activity and thus can be used for the treatment and/or prevention of cancer, in particular colorectal cancer, pancreatic cancer and glioblastoma. Furthermore, the present invention relates to a drug delivery system consisting of calcium phosphate nanoparticles functionalized with said bioactive molecules, preferably obtained from an extract of Euphorbia pekinensis. The invention also relates to a plant-derived ethanol extract obtained from the degreased powder of mature euphorbia pekinensis seeds.

column12: USE OF CK2 INHIBITOR FOR THE TREATMENT AND CHEMOSENSIBILIZATION OF REFRACTORY TUMORS TO ANTICANCER DRUGS
column13: The present invention relates to a pharmaceutical combination that includes a casein kinase 2 phosphorylation inhibitor (called p15) and cytostatics used in cancer chemotherapy, which are administered simultaneously, separately or sequentially. The preferred cytostatics are platinums, taxans, vinca alkaloids, 5-fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, etoposide, mitomycin C, imatinib, iressa and velcade (bortezomib). Synergy between peptide p15 and the anticancer chemical compounds means that the effective concentration of each cytostatic in the combination is between 1 and 2 orders of magnitude less than that corresponding to cytostatics alone. Consequently, the combination described in the invention has a much lower toxicity than that reported for anticancer cytostatics, which represents a crucial advantage in their use in cancer treatment. Additionally, administered sequentially, the combination gives rise to the chemosensitization of refractory tumours to the cytostatics mentioned by means of pre-treatment with peptide p15.

column12: Pharmaceutical combination for the treatment and/or chemosensibilization of refractory tumors to anticancer drugs
column13: This invention is related to a pharmaceutical combination that contains a Casein kinase 2 (CK2) peptide inhibitor (termed P15) along with the standard chemotherapeutic drugs used in cancer treatment and which are administered together, separated or sequentially. The chemothearapeutic drugs include cisplatin, taxol, alkaloids from Vinca, 5-fluorouracil, doxorubicin, cyclophosphamide, etoposide, mitomycin C, imatinib, iressa and velcade (bortezomib). The synergism between the P15 peptide and the anticancer drugs achieves an efficient concentration of each cytostatic drug in the combination which is from 10- to 100-fold lower than that for each cytostatic drug alone. The pharmaceutical combination described in this invention exhibits lower toxicity compared to that reported by the anticancer therapeutics and therefore, it represents a crucial advantage for its use in cancer therapy. Furthermore, the sequential administration of this pharmaceutical combination through the pretreatment with the P15 peptide leads to the chemo sensibilization of refractory tumors to the anticancer therapeutics.

column12: USE OF CK 2 INHIBITOR FOR TREATMENT AND CHEMICAL SENSITIZATION OF TUMOR UNRESPONSIVE TO ANTICANCER AGENT
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To evade chemotherapy resistance of a tumor to a cell proliferation inhibitor.SOLUTION: This invention relates to a method for combined use for administering simultaneously, individually or sequentially a combination of agents containing a casein kinase 2 phosphorylated inhibitor (called as p 15) and a cell proliferation inhibitor used in cancer chemotherapy. A preferable cell proliferation inhibitor is platinum, taxane, Vinca major L. genus alkaloid, 5-fluorouracil, Doxorubicin, Cyclophosphamide, Etoposide, mitomycin C, imatinib, Iressa and velcade (bortezomib). A synergistic effect between the peptide p 15 and an anticancer compound means that the effective concentration of each cell proliferation inhibitor in the method for combined use is lower by 1-2 figures than an effective concentration corresponding to a cell proliferation inhibitor as a single agent. Resultantly, the combination described in this invention has far lower toxicity than toxicity reported relative to an anticancer cell proliferation inhibitor, and the fact is an important advantage for the use thereof in cancer treatment. Further, sequential administration brings about chemical sensitization by premedication of the peptide p 15 of a tumor unresponsive to the anticancer cell proliferation inhibitor.

column12: DRUG DELIVERY SYSTEM BASED ON CALCIUM PHOSPHATE NANOPARTICLES FUNCTIONALIZED WITH BIOACTIVE COMPOUNDS FROM EUPHORBIA EXTRACT AND THE USES THEREOF
column13: The present invention relates to a composition comprising the bioactive molecules esculetin and euphorbetin, which present antitumor activity, so it may be used for the treatment and/or prevention of cancer, especially for colorectal, pancreatic and glioblastoma. Furthermore, it relates to a drug delivery system composed of nanoparticles of calcium phosphate functionalized with said bioactive molecules, preferably obtained from a Euphorbia extract. The invention also refers to the obtaining of an ethanolic extract of plant origin from defatted flour of mature seed of Euphorbia.
